 Hvala, Hvala, Hvala!

285
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:53,280
 Hvala, Hvala, Hvala, Hvala!

286
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:55,280
 Hvala, Hvala, Hvala, Hvala, Hvala!

287
00:26:55,280 --> 00:27:02,060
 is also much wider in terms of topics, banking union, economic union, fiscal union, democratic union.

288
00:27:02,060 --> 00:27:06,720
 So anything we discuss today, and it will get a bit more specific in a minute,

289
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:15,080
 don't forget that this is a part of an overall picture, an overall effort to make the EU and the euro area

290
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:18,940
 a more stable and a more prosperous area in the world economy.

291
00:27:18,940 --> 00:27:24,940
 So let me go to the outline, and as you see, it's relatively simple.

292
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:28,980
 And it's filled with acronyms and abbreviations.

293
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:35,040
 We talk about the SSM, Single Supervisor Mechanism, the SRV, the Single Resolution Board,

294
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:39,080
 and EDIS, our proposal for European Deposit Insurance Scheme.

295
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:48,480
 The whole process, as you will see, can become extremely technical, extremely detailed in technical issues.

296
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:54,480
 But don't forget, overall, as I say, the ambition is always to make the system more stable,

297
00:27:54,480 --> 00:28:00,040
 sound and conducive to smooth development of the economic union.

298
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:07,240
 Let me also go briefly back to put the topic into a perspective.

299
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:09,180
 We do have a single currency.

300
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:18,020
 We have set up the Single Supervisory Board and Single Supervisory Mechanism since last November 2014,

301
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:21,580
 which is located in the ECB.

302
00:28:21,580 --> 00:28:30,580
 We have set up the Single Resolution Mechanism since January 2015, and it's becoming operational now since 2016.

303
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:35,580
 And the Commission has recently proposed the European Deposit Insurance Scheme.

304
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:41,140
 And we are also, of course, talking about the common backstop, as Governor Vucic already has indicated.

305
00:28:41,140 --> 00:28:46,700
 So let me put all these elements into one picture.

306
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:54,260
 Everything is based on what we call the Single Rulebook for Banking and Financial Business of the EU 28.

307
00:28:54,260 --> 00:28:59,260
 That includes the Capital Requirements Regulation Directives.

308
00:28:59,260 --> 00:29:06,260
 It includes the Banking Recovery and Restructuring Directive and the Directive on Deposit Guarantee Scheme.

309
00:29:06,260 --> 00:29:14,820
 So this is something, this should be the foundation, this should be the foundation of this, you know, edifice, the House of Banking Union.

310
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:22,820
 And on this foundation, we have the Single Supervisory Mechanism, which is for the EU 19, so the 19 euro area countries,

311
00:29:22,820 --> 00:29:28,220
 as well as any other non-euro area country that chooses to participate in this mechanism.

312
00:29:28,220 --> 00:29:37,180
 We have the Single Resolution Board and the Single Resolution Fund, again, open to participation by any non-euro area member,

313
00:29:37,180 --> 00:29:41,220
 and mandatory for all members of the euro area.

314
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:47,380
 And as I've said, we have proposed a European Deposit Insurance Scheme under the same conditions.

315
00:29:47,380 --> 00:29:56,260
 Okay, let me start with the Single Supervisory Mechanism, just to give you a broad overview of how it is set up.

316
00:29:56,260 --> 00:30:08,420
 It is set up under the ECB in cooperation with the National Supervisors, and I think that is a very important element of all elements that we will talk about today.

317
00:30:08,420 --> 00:30:16,020
 You know, all these issues in banking regulation, banking supervision cannot be centralized anywhere, not in Frankfurt, not in Brussels anywhere.

318
00:30:16,020 --> 00:30:22,300
 So it always rests very strongly on the cooperation with national agencies and national supervisors.

319
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:32,460
 So in this case, in the Single Supervisory Mechanism, we have the exchange between the ECB, the SSM part, and the National Participating Member States.

320
00:30:32,460 --> 00:30:43,740
 And there is a coordination via the EBA, European Banking Authority, with the supervisors of non-participating member states.

321
00:30:43,740 --> 00:30:49,900
 Just briefly on the key task that the ECB has to fulfill.

322
00:30:49,900 --> 00:30:51,900
 Who is being supervised directly by the SSMs?

323
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:58,900
 Of course, the big banks, the large banks, with large assets important relative to national GDP.

324
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:03,900
 Certainly if they are important relative to their own domestic banking sector.

325
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:12,060
 The ECB under the SSM framework decides about licenses, you know, authorization, withdrawal.

326
00:31:12,060 --> 00:31:16,060
 It sets the requirements on capital leverage, liquidity governance.

327
00:31:16,060 --> 00:31:24,220
 There is consolidated supervision for conglomerates, you know, any wider cross-border banking businesses.

328
00:31:24,220 --> 00:31:29,900
 The ECB decides on the, or the SSM decides on the intervention measures, where a bank breaches requirements.

329
00:31:29,900 --> 00:31:34,700
 You know, what do we do if, you know, the requirements are not being complied with?

330
00:31:34,700 --> 00:31:40,060
 Importantly, there's what we call the macro-prudential tasks.

331
00:31:40,060 --> 00:31:44,380
 It's not only about micro-prudential, it's not about institution by institution.

332
00:31:44,380 --> 00:31:51,740
 But the past crisis has told us that, you know, bank supervision has an important spillover aspect.

333
00:31:51,740 --> 00:31:55,180
 You know, what happens in a single bank does not only affect a single bank.

334
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:59,980
 It always affects the entire system in a country or even across countries.

335
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:04,220
 So you do need to always think about what is the macro impact.

336
00:32:04,220 --> 00:32:06,460
 And that's what we call the macro-prudential tasks.

337
00:32:06,460 --> 00:32:14,940
 And the ECB under the ESM also talks about the mandate separation in the area of trading.

338
00:32:14,940 --> 00:32:18,380
 The final point may deserve some attention.

339
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:24,860
 Anything that is not explicitly conferred to the ECB remains with the national supervisors.

340
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:32,780
 So the national supervisors remain in place even if the SSM and all the related tasks are fully

341
00:32:32,780 --> 00:32:38,620
 operational and are fully carried out, then still the national supervisors will remain in place

342
00:32:38,620 --> 00:32:40,540
 and will have a very important task.

343
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:44,220
 Okay.

344
00:32:44,220 --> 00:32:47,020
 Turn to the single resolution mechanism.

345
00:32:47,020 --> 00:32:50,540
 It mirrors in a way the single supervisor mechanism.

346
00:32:50,540 --> 00:32:55,260
 So once you've, you know, agreed on how you want to carry out the supervision,

347
00:32:55,260 --> 00:33:00,220
 you want to know also what do we do in case the bank fails and we need to take care of it.

348
00:33:00,220 --> 00:33:06,380
 So the bank that are under the mechanism are the same as we have under the SSM.

349
00:33:06,940 --> 00:33:13,900
 The board of the SRM is directly responsible for large banks and cross-border banks.

350
00:33:13,900 --> 00:33:20,140
 So anything that affects the Euro area as a whole or the Euro area in terms of several countries

351
00:33:20,140 --> 00:33:30,140
 will be handled by the SRB board and the national restructuring agencies remain responsible for all

352
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:30,700
 other banks.

353
00:33:30,700 --> 00:33:34,700
 But in the end, as I say, it's a single mechanism.

354
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:40,860
 So in the end, of course, we need to be sure that, you know, whatever is done is acceptable

355
00:33:41,420 --> 00:33:42,940
 for also for the entire group.

356
00:33:42,940 --> 00:33:47,820
 This is a little schematic presentation.

357
00:33:47,820 --> 00:33:51,020
 As I was saying at the start, the whole thing is extremely complicated.

358
00:33:51,020 --> 00:33:55,820
 But I think this graph shows you overall the whole idea.

359
00:33:55,820 --> 00:33:58,940
 At the center, we have the single resolution board.

360
00:33:58,940 --> 00:33:59,980
 Let me see if I can.

361
00:33:59,980 --> 00:34:09,740
 Single resolution board, which can instruct national authorities to resolve a failed bank.

362
00:34:10,860 --> 00:34:18,380
 And of course, under the BRD, we now have this what also governor Vucic referred to the the bail-in.

363
00:34:18,380 --> 00:34:24,460
 So we do not no longer ask taxpayers to cut up the money for failed banks.

364
00:34:24,460 --> 00:34:32,700
 But we have a very important component of primary involvement of of lenders to the bank under different

365
00:34:32,700 --> 00:34:33,820
 levels.

366
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:40,220
 And the ECB is involved via the SSM and the national supervisors.

367
00:34:40,860 --> 00:34:43,980
 And they can give the notification to the single resolution board.

368
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:49,100
 So whenever the ECB and the SSM framework feels that, you know, things are not going right,

369
00:34:49,100 --> 00:34:54,140
 capital has been exhausted, you know, the quitting situation is getting serious,

370
00:34:54,140 --> 00:35:01,820
 then it will contact and notify the SRB, which will then take the respective action,

371
00:35:01,820 --> 00:35:05,660
 always with involvement of the commission and the council.

372
00:35:06,780 --> 00:35:12,620
 The financing of the whole system is done by all banks, which contribute to the single

373
00:35:12,620 --> 00:35:19,660
 resolution fund to set up a sufficient, you know, fund to actually allow the

374
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:23,420
 resolution of banks without shattering market confidence.

375
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:29,660
 Okay, how does it look in public, sorry, in practice?

376
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:34,860
 ECB determines if a bank is failing likely to fail.

377
00:35:34,860 --> 00:35:41,900
 There is also a provision that the board itself may decide to launch the processes.

378
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:47,100
 Of course, all these issues about, you know, governance of the balance of power is extremely

379
00:35:47,100 --> 00:35:53,020
 difficult and it's extremely, you know, prone to fine-tuning who does what, when, under what

380
00:35:53,020 --> 00:35:58,860
 conditions. So all these things will need to come into play and be understood fully once everything

381
00:35:58,860 --> 00:36:05,420
 is fully operational. The board then assesses if there is a systemic threat and if there is no other

382
00:36:05,420 --> 00:36:10,620
 private solution. You know, that these are the conditions for the single resolution board and the

383
00:36:10,620 --> 00:36:18,220
 fund to come into play. And then the board adopts the resolution scheme as a resolution and, of course,

384
00:36:18,220 --> 00:36:24,460
 important to the funding measures. That is then submitted to the commission and the council for

385
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:30,860
 endorsement or objective. So in the end, it will remain a political problem and a political question.

386
00:36:30,860 --> 00:36:35,900
 It's clear, the council needs to be involved. But I think the whole process shows that there's a lot of

387
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:41,500
 technical expertise beyond the national borders, which flows into this process. And I think that

388
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:47,420
 is important. We have seen in the past crisis that banking supervision was maybe in some instances too

389
00:36:47,420 --> 00:36:52,860
 close to the national authorities and the national political interests. There is still political interest

390
00:36:52,860 --> 00:36:59,500
 coming in in this process, but it comes at the very end after, you know, independent and well-regarded

391
00:36:59,500 --> 00:37:04,220
 institutions have done their technical work and have come to their own conclusions.

392
00:37:04,220 --> 00:37:14,780
 Okay, let me look at the findings side. Of course, you know, if you if you want to talk about resolution,

393
00:37:14,780 --> 00:37:19,980
 you have to talk about, you know, do we have the money? Who comes up with the money? So we need to

394
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:26,860
 have the financing available immediately and certainly also while the single resolution fund is being

395
00:37:26,860 --> 00:37:34,700
 completed by the contributions by the banks. So we need something as of now, even if it's a temporary

396
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:41,100
 solution, each member states backs the national compartment in the single resolution funds. So we have the

397
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:47,260
 single resolution fund where bank contributions are being channeled and which these bank contributions

398
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:54,700
 build up over time. But for the time for the intermediate time, each member state, you know, is, you know, is compelled

399
00:37:54,700 --> 00:38:03,420
 to back it up by own guarantee payments in case there's a large withdrawal. There's no mutualization for the time being.

400
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:10,780
 So for the current time, it's still national compartment. It's still only national money that flows into that. But of course,

401
00:38:10,780 --> 00:38:16,540
 since we talk about a single banking union in a single European market, at some point,

402
00:38:16,540 --> 00:38:22,060
 we need to talk about the common backstop. I think it's clear if you have a banking union with banks

403
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:28,060
 being operational in the whole EU-EU area, then at some point you have to talk about also a common

404
00:38:28,060 --> 00:38:34,780
 backstop which is available to all and every single individual bank across the union. It should be

405
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:41,180
 mutualized by at the latest 2024. And as we have heard before, this is a discussion which is ongoing

406
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:45,820
 and it's not an easy discussion. It's about, you know, large amounts of money, but it has to be, you know,

407
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:47,340
 pushed forward.

408
00:38:47,340 --> 00:38:55,260
 Okay, let me come to the European Deposit Insurance Scheme, the third pillar as we call it of the

409
00:38:55,260 --> 00:39:03,180
 banking union. And as we've also heard before, progress has been there, you know, there is some

410
00:39:03,180 --> 00:39:09,100
 progress, but it's again, it's a difficult discussion and several policy players, several involved parties

411
00:39:09,100 --> 00:39:15,100
 have already made very clear statements on what they consider necessary conditions before they even would want to

412
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:21,340
 talk about these issues. Other stakeholders have expressed more or less the opposite opinion.

413
00:39:21,340 --> 00:39:26,620
 So this is a clearly political process and will take some time to go on. But I think we need to push

414
00:39:26,620 --> 00:39:31,660
 ahead because a banking union without a deposit guarantee scheme is very difficult to imagine.

415
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:36,140
 Okay, what are the key principles of the Commission proposal?

416
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:47,260
 First of all, there we are, this should only go ahead once the directive on deposit or national

417
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:52,540
 deposit guarantee schemes is fully in place. So it cannot be that some countries would not even

418
00:39:52,540 --> 00:39:58,140
 complete their own homework for their own national deposit guarantee schemes and then already start to

419
00:39:58,140 --> 00:40:03,340
 claim money from the European Deposit Insurance Scheme. That is not acceptable. So this is a clear precondition.

420
00:40:03,340 --> 00:40:09,500
 There should not be higher costs for the banking sector overall. Banks are paying in the national schemes.

421
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:15,100
 The idea is to shift gradually these contributions, but keep the overall amount limited.

422
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:21,580
 All banks should be covered, but there should be risk-based contributions after the third year.

423
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:27,740
 It's similar to the national schemes where typically you also have risk-based contributions.

424
00:40:27,740 --> 00:40:33,740
 The difference being that at some point also the type of risk assessment should be

425
00:40:33,740 --> 00:40:41,740
 harmonized because otherwise you get distortions in markets. If very risky banks are paying very high

426
00:40:41,740 --> 00:40:48,220
 contributions in some systems, but you know very low, relatively low premium relative to their own risk

427
00:40:48,220 --> 00:40:54,060
 in other areas, then this would distort the market process. So you want some harmonization at this point.

428
00:40:54,060 --> 00:41:00,780
 Risk sharing and risk reduction should go together. This is clearly one of the major political discussions

429
00:41:00,780 --> 00:41:08,060
 currently at the commission line. It's clearly this should go in parallel. Other stakeholders say there

430
00:41:08,060 --> 00:41:13,660
 should be a sequencing, you know, risk reduction should come first and then only then we can talk about risk sharing.

431
00:41:13,660 --> 00:41:19,660
 Okay, I will not go more deeply into that, but I think it's clear that there should be a clear link between the two.

432
00:41:20,380 --> 00:41:26,300
 And of course it's a there's legacy issues. There are banks which are already

433
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:31,260
 you know, not not fully there where they should be in terms of capitalization and risk reduction.

434
00:41:31,260 --> 00:41:37,340
 So there's something that needs to be dealt with while promoting the overall progress towards the deposit

435
00:41:37,340 --> 00:41:45,580
 insurance scheme. We foresee three stages: a reinsurance step in the first three years of existence,

436
00:41:45,580 --> 00:41:51,260
 then what we call a co-insurance system and then the full insurance system again by 2024. You've seen

437
00:41:51,260 --> 00:41:57,900
 before this year 2024 is becoming kind of the focal point of the whole process. We hope very much that

438
00:41:57,900 --> 00:42:02,860
 we can stick to that, but as was said earlier deadlines are always a tricky thing to talk about.

439
00:42:02,860 --> 00:42:08,780
 What is reinsurance? Reinsurance means that the risks remain largely national.

440
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:15,340
 So moral hazard, legacy issues, so the issues that you know hamper current deposit insurance

441
00:42:15,340 --> 00:42:22,140
 aspects now would remain at the national level and the EDIS, the deposit insurance scheme, would only

442
00:42:22,140 --> 00:42:29,980
 provide the liquidity if the national scheme has exhausted its resources and of course, as I said before,

443
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:35,820
 the directive on deposit guarantee schemes has been fully implemented. So this is very much a very gradual

444
00:42:36,620 --> 00:42:44,940
 step towards the European system. It's basically a fallback option. Once the national scheme is exploited

445
00:42:44,940 --> 00:42:50,780
 and certain other conditions are fulfilled, at least we know, yes, there will be money from Europe. So it is a

446
00:42:50,780 --> 00:43:00,060
 European angle to the process, but it's still very much based on the on the national arrangements.

447
00:43:00,060 --> 00:43:07,260
 Yeah, other caps and safeguards, so there is quite some protection at this stage. Co-insurance is a step

448
00:43:07,260 --> 00:43:18,300
 beyond that. Co-insurance means that the EDIS, the European part of the system, will jump in at the same

449
00:43:18,300 --> 00:43:30,620
 time as the national schemes. And this will rise gradually over time. So whatever the national schemes

450
00:43:30,620 --> 00:43:36,540
 payout will be augmented, will be completed by the European scheme. There is some mutualization

451
00:43:36,540 --> 00:43:43,500
 and some of the risk is actually then by this stage already transferred to the to the European level.

452
00:43:43,500 --> 00:43:48,540
 And the degree of cover will increase over the four years. So the idea is to build it up gradually,

453
00:43:48,540 --> 00:43:54,220
 start with a small amount around 20% and then build it up over the four years. So then by the end

454
00:43:54,220 --> 00:44:01,420
 of the system of this four year period in 2024, we would be there and have a full, fully mutualized,

455
00:44:01,420 --> 00:44:03,820
 fully operational European system.

456
00:44:07,100 --> 00:44:16,300
 I don't know if this is easy to read. The idea is that we have the national contributions to the national

457
00:44:16,300 --> 00:44:24,540
 schemes and part of these contributions goes from the start to the European Deposit Insurance Scheme.

458
00:44:24,540 --> 00:44:30,700
 This is what we say here in the box. And this part, the share of the national contributions that goes to

459
00:44:30,700 --> 00:44:39,020
 the European scheme grows over time. So until in the end, we end up with a purely European scheme.

460
00:44:39,020 --> 00:44:45,660
 So by 2024, we have a European scheme, which is fully financed by the banking sector and banks do not

461
00:44:45,660 --> 00:44:52,860
 pay anything to the national schemes, which are fading out by the time and everything is completely taken over by the European schemes.

462
00:44:54,940 --> 00:45:04,060
 So just to recap where we are and just to put it again into the bigger picture, we talked about the points 2, 3 and 4.

463
00:45:04,060 --> 00:45:13,660
 We talked about reducing national options, stronger role for the SSM and the ECB in the application also of macro potential tools.

464
00:45:13,660 --> 00:45:21,260
 We talked about the single resolution board and the single resolution fund and we talked about the deposit guarantee schemes.

465
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:30,380
 At the same time and before the process and we alluded to that before, we have to make sure that the BRD and the DSG-SD are fully implemented.

466
00:45:30,380 --> 00:45:37,100
 So there can be no progress unless all these directives and regulations are fully implemented.

467
00:45:37,100 --> 00:45:42,380
 There must be a level playing field. There's no point in proceeding with harmonization and mutualization

468
00:45:42,380 --> 00:45:46,700
 in unless we agree that every country has done their homework.

469
00:45:46,700 --> 00:45:51,500
 And the whole set is completed by other potential measures.

470
00:45:51,500 --> 00:45:59,100
 And we are talking and we will probably talk later today also about putting the banking union into the wider framework.

471
00:45:59,100 --> 00:46:01,180
 We've heard it about the five present report.

472
00:46:01,180 --> 00:46:04,220
 We should also importantly talk about capital markets union.

473
00:46:04,220 --> 00:46:15,340
 One aspect why the financial crisis hit so catastrophically in the EU's large major role of the banking sector.

474
00:46:15,340 --> 00:46:18,380
 Why do we not have more equity financing?

475
00:46:18,380 --> 00:46:23,820
 Why does every or almost 70% of corporate financing have to go through the banking sector?

476
00:46:23,820 --> 00:46:30,460
 This is one distinguishing feature to the US where the share of the banking financing is much lower in the corporate sector.

477
00:46:30,460 --> 00:46:36,620
 So that anything that happens in the banking sector is a problem in itself but does not necessarily mean

478
00:46:36,620 --> 00:46:40,700
 that the whole corporate financing sector is going into the abyss.

479
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:46,060
 So that is one aspect that should be talked about.

480
00:46:46,060 --> 00:46:51,340
 Capital markets union, risk-weighting, bank funding.

481
00:46:51,340 --> 00:46:57,100
 So all the aspects that make the whole banking sector more stable and allow to develop a more,

482
00:46:57,100 --> 00:47:01,580
 maybe more balanced growth model for the financial sector overall.

483
00:47:01,580 --> 00:47:04,620
 Okay, what is the outlook?

484
00:47:04,620 --> 00:47:10,700
 As we were saying before, banking union discussions are ongoing in the Council and the European Parliament.

485
00:47:10,700 --> 00:47:17,500
 The deposit insurance proposal is being discussed together with the SRS backstop idea.

486
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:19,580
 These two are the separate things.

487
00:47:19,580 --> 00:47:22,860
 You know, they are frequently mentioned together but still,

488
00:47:22,860 --> 00:47:25,340
 in terms of purpose, they are separate things.

489
00:47:25,340 --> 00:47:30,380
 They may be administratively managed by the same institution that you can think about that.

490
00:47:30,380 --> 00:47:33,420
 But conceptually, I think it should be clear that this is not the same thing.

491
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:41,820
 And then risk reduction, of course, bank exposure to sovereign risks is one aspect

492
00:47:41,820 --> 00:47:43,900
 that is clearly also on the agenda.

493
00:47:43,900 --> 00:47:46,300
 All these things are being discussed, discussions are ongoing,

494
00:47:46,300 --> 00:47:50,220
 and I think we should make sure that progress continues.

495
00:47:50,220 --> 00:47:54,620
 Thank you very much.

496
00:47:54,620 --> 00:48:09,680
 Dobar dan.

497
00:48:09,680 --> 00:48:17,440
 Kao što možete vidjeti, moj ime je Vedran Šošić.

498
00:48:17,440 --> 00:48:23,480
 Ja sam viceguvernar ovdje u HMB-u, za one koji me ne znaju i koji nisu detaljni upoznati s mojim radom.

499
00:48:23,980 --> 00:48:29,800
 Ja sam zadužen za istraživanje i financijsku, što uključuje i financijsku stabilnost i statistiku.

500
00:48:29,800 --> 00:48:34,980
 Znači, na neki način ja sam dobio zadatak ovdje kao nepristan promatrač,

501
00:48:34,980 --> 00:48:44,660
 jer nisam zadužen ni za superviziju, ni za sanaciju banaka, ali istovremeno i ne zainteresiram promatrač.

502
00:48:44,660 --> 00:48:51,500
 Dati jedan pregled načina na koji mi ovdje u HMB-u razmišljamo o Bankovnoj uniji.

503
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:58,740
 O koristima i troškovima, odnosno nekakvim potencijalnim, mi o njima razmišljamo više kao izazovima,

504
00:48:58,740 --> 00:49:04,340
 sudjelovanja u mehanizmu bliske kooperacije i prije nego što Hrvatska uvede euro.

505
00:49:04,340 --> 00:49:08,540
 Zašto smo rekli da je strateški cilj i nešto čemu bi mi trebali težiti.

506
00:49:09,480 --> 00:49:20,680
 U ovoj moj prezentaciji imam sreću što je gospodin Rotar dao vrlo detaljan prikaz strukture i funkcioniranja Bankovne unije.

507
00:49:20,820 --> 00:49:25,940
 Tako da sada znate apsolutno sve što se tiče Bankovne unije.

508
00:49:25,940 --> 00:49:38,040
 Tako da se ja mogu malo više koncentrirati na učinke Bankovne unije na zemlje članice Europske unije koje nisu u europodručju.

509
00:49:38,160 --> 00:49:40,820
 Znači koje nisu joj članice Monetarne unije.

510
00:49:40,820 --> 00:49:49,380
 U tome ću se najprije osvrnuti na koristi za koje znamo da postoje, bez toga ne bi bilo Bankovne unije.

511
00:49:49,380 --> 00:49:58,660
 Međutim da ću jedan malo specifičan pogled na izazove sudjelovanja u mehanizmu bliske suradnje koji gospodin Rotar nije predstavio.

512
00:49:58,660 --> 00:50:10,240
 I također ono što ja mogu ovdje reći je nešto ispričati o dosadašnjim iskustvima i našim stavljima u pogledu suradnje i perspektive priključivanja Bankovnoj uniji.

513
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:15,760
 Znači mi imamo već nekako iskustvo suradnje uz postavljanje ono što se kaže track record.

514
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:24,180
 Znači imamo nekakvu institucionaliziranu suradnju s mehanizmima i institucijama Bankovne unije.

515
00:50:27,240 --> 00:50:39,880
 Najprije nešto o potencijalnim koristima. Čuli smo da je u temelju Bankovne unije usleđena bankovna regulativa i konvergencija supervizorske prakse.

516
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:53,860
 Znači svi oni propisi o kojima je govorio gospodin Rotar od uredbe i direktive o kapitalnim zahtjevima, od direktive odnosno smjernice o oporavku i sanaciji banaka,

517
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:59,760
 pa do teh regulatornih tehničkih standarda koje donosi EBA. To je nešto što vrijedi za sve zemlje članice.

518
00:50:59,760 --> 00:51:08,500
 Evropske unije, neopisno tome jesu li one članice Bankovne unije ili su kao Hrvatska još uvijek izvan Bankovne unije.

519
00:51:08,500 --> 00:51:14,800
 Pri tome je bitno napomenuti da još uvijek postoji jedan znatan broj nacionalnih diskrecija.

520
00:51:16,980 --> 00:51:27,300
 Za sada ih ima nekakvih 80-ak od prilike nacionalnih opcija i diskrecija, od čega je dijel tranzicijskih, znači tijekom vremena će nestati,

521
00:51:27,300 --> 00:51:32,420
 međutim 60-ak tih nacionalnih diskrecija i opcija je stalno.

522
00:51:32,420 --> 00:51:37,020
 I one su posebno bitne za zemlje koje ne sudjeluju u Bankovnoj uniji.

523
00:51:37,020 --> 00:51:44,260
 Ali ipak u odnosu na regulativu i praksu prije uveđenja Bankovne unije,

524
00:51:44,260 --> 00:51:48,800
 stupanj harmonizacije i konvergencije je nesumljivo puno više.

525
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:53,160
 Ono što bi Bankovna unija trebala donijeti je bolji regulatorni okver.

526
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:59,280
 Znači okver koji će znatno smanjiti vjerojatnost izbijanja budućih financijskih kriza

527
00:51:59,280 --> 00:52:04,300
 i koji će olakšati kapacitet ne samo nacionalnih zemalja članica,

528
00:52:04,300 --> 00:52:10,540
 nego i novo stvorenih institucija na razini unije da se nose s tim krizama ako slučajno do njih dođe.

529
00:52:10,540 --> 00:52:16,420
 Ono što Bankovna unija donosi je fiskal backstop, fiskalni zaštitni mehanizam.

530
00:52:16,560 --> 00:52:21,840
 Znači više se ne može dogoditi da kriza koja se može dogodi u jednoj zemlji članici

531
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:24,760
 bude prevelika za nju da se može uopće nositi s njom.

532
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:31,060
 Iza te zemlje stoje mehanizmi uspostavljeni na razini Bankovne unije

533
00:52:31,060 --> 00:52:35,160
 koje daju vjerodostojnosti, koje olakšavaju nošenje s krizama.

534
00:52:35,160 --> 00:52:39,060
 Znači sve je to nešto što donosi sudjelovanje u Bankovnoj uniji zemljama članicama.

535
00:52:39,060 --> 00:52:46,520
 Nadalje, otklanjanje. Čuli smo da Europska sredična banka blisko surađuje

536
00:52:46,520 --> 00:52:50,880
 sa supervizorima na terenu iz nacionalnih sredičnih banaka.

537
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:55,560
 Međutim, više unutar Bankovne unije više ne postoje koleđe supervizora

538
00:52:55,560 --> 00:53:01,340
 na kojima je se znala događati prilično mukotrbna koordinacija

539
00:53:01,340 --> 00:53:09,120
 ponekad čak i uz posredovanje jebe. Znači cijeli proces teče puno glađe, puno jednostavnije, puno bi trebao biti učinkovitiji.

540
00:53:09,120 --> 00:53:20,580
 Banke bi mogle imati znatne uštede. Premda je volumen regulative narastao, Bankovna unija istovremeno donosi nekakve uštede za banke.

541
00:53:20,980 --> 00:53:25,340
 Pogotovo za banke koje posluju u više jurisdikcije, u više zemalja članica.

542
00:53:25,340 --> 00:53:33,180
 Znači više se banke ne suočavaju s nekoliko različitih setova izvješća za svakog regulatora, drugačija izvješća.

543
00:53:33,520 --> 00:53:43,820
 Imaju samo jedan set regulative i jednog supervizora koji im dolazi. Ne dolazi im više nekoliko supervizora koji provjeravaju njihovo poslovanje.

544
00:53:43,820 --> 00:53:51,140
 Sve to umanjuje potrebu za angažmanom resursa i troškove za bankarski sektor, što nije za odbaciti.

545
00:53:51,140 --> 00:53:57,520
 Također, nešto što smatramo i osobito koristim, što je također spomenuo usp. gospodin Roter,

546
00:53:57,520 --> 00:54:05,400
 je da bankovna unija nosi potencijal internalizacije nekakvih troškova i koristi makroprudencijalne politike.

547
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:11,520
 Imali smo u Hrvatskoj do 2008. godine situaciju vrlo visokog rasta kredita.

548
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:19,820
 Kad je HMB svojim makroprudencijalnim mjerama nastoja ograničiti pretjerani rast kredita,

549
00:54:19,820 --> 00:54:27,320
 banke su na različite načine zaobilazile ta ograničenja, bilo kroz izravno prekogranično kreditiranje.

550
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:30,640
 Ali na neke druge načine imali smo regulatornu arbitražu.

551
00:54:30,640 --> 00:54:38,180
 U hipotecki, naravno to tek treba vidjeti, u situaciji kad je hrvatska članica bankovne unije,

552
00:54:38,180 --> 00:54:42,580
 može se dogoditi da Europska srediča banka vidi što se događa u Hrvatskoj

553
00:54:42,580 --> 00:54:49,460
 i sugerira zemljama u kojima posluju banke koje teku sredstva u Hrvatskoj

554
00:54:49,460 --> 00:54:53,720
 i generiraju taj prekomjerni kreditni rast da učine nešto, da poduzmu nekakve mjere

555
00:54:53,720 --> 00:54:56,920
 koje bi ograničile taj prekomjeran kreditni rast.

556
00:54:56,920 --> 00:55:02,640
 Znači imamo nekakav dodatni mehanizam koji jača nacionalnu makroprudencijalnu politiku.

557
00:55:02,640 --> 00:55:07,900
 I sve to skupa bi u perspektivi moglo spustiti troškove.

558
00:55:07,900 --> 00:55:13,100
 Znači jedan sigurniji, stabilniji bankovni sustav bi mogao smanjiti troškove,

559
00:55:13,100 --> 00:55:18,360
 mogao rezultirati nižnim troškovem na financiranje, što je isto korist od sudjelovanja u bankovnoj udu.

560
00:55:20,360 --> 00:55:29,380
 Naravno, te sve koristi bi trebale do punog izražaja doći tek u trenutku kad se bankovna unija kompletira,

561
00:55:29,380 --> 00:55:33,560
 kad se dovrši. Znači ona će naćiti jedinstvenu superviziju u nekim slučajevima,

562
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:42,720
 pogotovo u situacijama kad su nekakvi nacionalni elementi utjecali na superviziju,

563
00:55:42,780 --> 00:55:55,520
 ta supervizija bi mogla biti istroža. Prevencija kumuliranja rizika i konzistentna sanacija će također

564
00:55:55,520 --> 00:56:03,060
 pridavniti financijskoj stabilnosti. Svi oni mehanizmi za solidarno dijeljanje rizika će jako koristiti

565
00:56:03,060 --> 00:56:09,220
 financijskoj stabilnosti u pojedinim zemljama članicama. I također ono što je dijelomično već napravljeno,

566
00:56:09,220 --> 00:56:14,100
 a radi se i dalje, otklanjanje negativne povratne sprege između banaka i države,

567
00:56:14,100 --> 00:56:22,060
 pri čemu ta negativna povratna sprega dijeluje u oba smjera. Više do sada napravljeno da bi se

568
00:56:22,060 --> 00:56:30,060
 ograničila negativna povratna sprega u smjeru od banaka, koja generira zarazu od banaka prema državi,

569
00:56:30,060 --> 00:56:36,000
 a sada se razmišlja i kako ograničiti mogućnost zaraze od nekakvih fiskalnih problema

570
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:41,340
 u pojedinoj zemlji članici da se preliju na banke koje posluju u toj zemlji članici.

571
00:56:42,480 --> 00:56:49,100
 Naravno, nije za sve zemlje jednako, prilačno priključiti se bankovne unije.

572
00:56:49,100 --> 00:56:55,300
 Neke će se možda priključiti od onih devet zemalja koje nisu trenutno.

573
00:56:55,300 --> 00:56:58,960
 Znači, neke će možda ući u mehanizam bliske suradnje, mada još nijedna nije ušla,

574
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:04,320
 neke možda neće. To je zato što oni koristi nisu jednake za sve zemlje članice.

575
00:57:04,440 --> 00:57:13,860
 Oni ovisi o karakteristikama te konkretne zemlje. Znači, ako su banki koje posluju u toj zemlji

576
00:57:13,860 --> 00:57:18,000
 jače integrirane sa bankama u bankovnoj uniji, u njihovom su vlasništu,

577
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:21,840
 onda je i veća korist od uslođene regulative i supervizorske prakse

578
00:57:21,840 --> 00:57:26,580
 i također i od internaliziranja troškova i koristi makroprudencijalne politike.

579
00:57:26,580 --> 00:57:30,760
 Također, ovisi i o karakteristikama nacionalne supervizije.

580
00:57:30,760 --> 00:57:36,720
 Znači, u nekim slučajevima jedinstveni supervizorski mehanizam može pridonijeti

581
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:45,680
 vjerodostojnosti i kvaliteti na neki način poduprijeti domaću superviziju

582
00:57:45,680 --> 00:57:49,480
 i povećava konzistentno supervizorske prakse.

583
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:56,800
 Također, u nekim slučajevima, Europska središnja banka može i sama potaknuti

584
00:57:56,800 --> 00:57:59,660
 zemlje članice da dijeluju mjeramo makroprudencijalne politike.

585
00:57:59,660 --> 00:58:03,480
 Ako zemlje do sada nisu bile sklone tome ili imaju neke druge barijere,

586
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:07,600
 Europska središnja banka može pitati svaku zemlju u kojoj primijeti

587
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:11,860
 generiranje makroekonomskih naravnoteža da poduzme nekakve mjere

588
00:58:11,860 --> 00:58:14,500
 koje će ograničiti kumuliranje tih naravnoteža.

589
00:58:14,500 --> 00:58:19,600
 Znači, ovisi zemlje koje su više koristile makroprudencijalnu politiku

590
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:24,320
 kao što je Hrvatska, vjerojatno će takve nekoj koristi, za njih će biti nešto manje.

591
00:58:26,180 --> 00:58:32,040
 Znamo da su banke u Hrvatskoj relativno visoko integrirane,

592
00:58:32,040 --> 00:58:37,820
 to nije samo u Hrvatskoj, u nizu zemalja su, u srednje istočne Evrope su banke

593
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:41,660
 vrlo snažno integrirane s bankama iz eurozone, u njihovom su vlasništvu konkretno.

594
00:58:41,660 --> 00:58:47,940
 Međutim, supervizija je u zemljama srednje istočne Evrope uglavnom bila kvalitetna,

595
00:58:47,940 --> 00:58:51,180
 se pokazala u dosadašnjem razlogu. Banke su kapitalizirane,

596
00:58:51,180 --> 00:58:57,080
 dobro kapitalizirane, razmeno profitabilne i ono što je bitno je da su

597
00:58:57,080 --> 00:59:01,240
 subsidijari, kao što je guverner spomenuo, s vremenom postali financijski

598
00:59:01,240 --> 00:59:06,000
 samodostatni, znači omjer kredita i depozita se uglavnom spustuju ispod 100%.

599
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:11,820
 Znači oni postuju na neki način već sada ti subsidijari kao samostalne banke,

600
00:59:11,820 --> 00:59:15,100
 a ne kao dijelovi, integralni dijelovi preko graničnih grupa.

601
00:59:15,100 --> 00:59:19,080
 Znači nekako financijska kriza je donijela do tog prelaska na model

602
00:59:19,080 --> 00:59:22,100
 samodostatnih subsidijara, bankovnih subsidijara.

603
00:59:22,100 --> 00:59:24,960
 I znamo da u zemljama srednje istočne Evrope nije bilo,

604
00:59:24,960 --> 00:59:28,340
 uglavnom nije bilo nikakvih potresa tijekom financijske krize.

605
00:59:28,340 --> 00:59:32,880
 Ono što je najslabija točka bankovnih sustava srednje istočne Evrope

606
00:59:32,880 --> 00:59:36,140
 je povišena razina loših kredita.

607
00:59:36,140 --> 00:59:42,920
 Međutim, mozak u Bankovnu uniju zapravo nije način da se riješi taj problem.

608
00:59:42,920 --> 00:59:48,220
 Za rješavanje problema viših kredita su bitne nacionalne stečajne procedure,

609
00:59:48,220 --> 00:59:51,160
 porezni tretman loših kredita i tako dalje.

610
00:59:51,160 --> 00:59:54,020
 Znači neke stvari koje dalje ostaju u domeni nacionalnih vlasti.

611
00:59:54,020 --> 01:00:00,720
 Evo, kao što sam spomenuo, crvenim stupcima su označene zemlje

612
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:02,520
 srednje istočne Evrope.

613
01:00:02,520 --> 01:00:07,440
 Uglavnom su stope ukupnog kapitala više nego u ostalnim zemljama.

614
01:00:08,020 --> 01:00:12,920
 Članicama Europske unije Hrvatska je tu bila pri vrhu, sad je i dalje iznad prosjeka,

615
01:00:12,920 --> 01:00:17,680
 međutim, nakon provedene konverzije kredita u švicarskom franku prošle godine

616
01:00:17,680 --> 01:00:22,740
 malo se približila prosjeku Europske unije po stope ukupnog kapitala.

617
01:00:22,740 --> 01:00:29,140
 Također, po povratu na kapital Hrvatska je po onim objavljenim brojkama za prošlo godine,

618
01:00:29,140 --> 01:00:37,020
 ovo su brojke za treće tromjeseće prošle godine, bile zapravo zemlja koja je imala najveće gubitke

619
01:00:37,020 --> 01:00:40,400
 u kojoj je bankovni sektor imao najveće gubitke nakon Grčke,

620
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:47,360
 međutim, ako korigiramo za jednokratne troške, za jednokratan trošak konverzije,

621
01:00:47,360 --> 01:00:53,540
 onda je povrat na kapital bio nešto niži od 5%, to je također blizu prosjeka Europske unije.

622
01:00:53,540 --> 01:00:59,820
 Po omjeru kredita i depozita vidite da su sve zemlje ispod omjera Srednje stranje Evrope,

623
01:00:59,820 --> 01:01:04,480
 ispod omjera od 100%, znači više nisu ovisne o financiranju od svojih matica

624
01:01:04,480 --> 01:01:10,240
 i ono po čemu, nepovoljno po čemu se ističu su povišene razine loših kredita.

625
01:01:10,240 --> 01:01:16,460
 Kao što smo rekli, to nije, bankovna unija nije mehanizam koji omogućava rješavanje loših kredita.

626
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:24,720
 Kao što smo čuli, jedan od glavnih izazova sudjelovanja u mehanizmu blizke suradnje

627
01:01:24,720 --> 01:01:30,440
 je činjenica da je bankovna unija nedovršen proces i uz još uvijek dosta nepoznanica.

628
01:01:30,440 --> 01:01:39,400
 Da figurativno se izrazim kao i guverner, znači to je kuća u kojoj je prizemlje useljivo,

629
01:01:39,400 --> 01:01:45,580
 prvi kat je u rohu, pa u fazi, a na drugom katu građevinski radovi su još u punom tijeku.

630
01:01:45,580 --> 01:01:51,820
 I sad sigurno da ćete dobro razmisliti prije nego što usilite u jednu kuću koja je tako nedovršena.

631
01:01:51,820 --> 01:01:58,760
 Znači, na papiru imamo dva stupa, međutim u praksi jedinstveni sanacijski mehanizam

632
01:01:58,760 --> 01:02:04,640
 još uvijek nije u potpunosti zaživio, znači on dijeluje,

633
01:02:04,640 --> 01:02:10,880
 međutim sanacijski koleđi se ne sastaju, još uvijek nemamo sanacijske planove

634
01:02:10,880 --> 01:02:15,380
 izrađene za velike prekogranične grupe koje posluje u Hrvatskoj.

635
01:02:15,380 --> 01:02:25,760
 Još jedna zapreka, barijera za odluku o uključivanje u mehanizam bliske suradnje

636
01:02:25,760 --> 01:02:27,880
 je i sudjelovanje u procesu odlučivanja.

637
01:02:27,880 --> 01:02:33,080
 Znači, nekako ultimativno zadnje tijelo koje donosi odluke je upravno viječe

638
01:02:33,080 --> 01:02:38,980
 Europske sredične banke, a zemlje koje nisu u eurozoni ne sjede u tom upravnom viječu

639
01:02:38,980 --> 01:02:44,000
 Europske sredične banke koje može poništiti odluku supervizijskog odbora SSM-a.

640
01:02:44,000 --> 01:02:50,020
 Jedino što preostaje zemlji u tom slučaju je napustiti bankovnu uniju

641
01:02:50,020 --> 01:02:55,020
 što može imati nekakve negativne reputacijske implikacije

642
01:02:55,020 --> 01:03:02,020
 i komplicira onda ponovno proces uključivanja ako se želimo uključiti ponovno u nekakve kasnije faze.

643
01:03:02,020 --> 01:03:10,440
 Još jedan problem iz perspektive zemlja koja nije članica europodručja je i pristup zajedničkom

644
01:03:10,440 --> 01:03:17,240
 fiskalnom zaštitnom mehanizmu. Znači, ISM, Europski stabilizacijski mehanizam, je međudržavni ugovor

645
01:03:17,240 --> 01:03:23,520
 između zemalja članica europodručja. Hrvatska nije potpisnica i ne sudjeluje u Europskom stabilizacijskom mehanizmu.

646
01:03:23,520 --> 01:03:29,840
 Znači, za Hrvatsku i druge zemlje koje bi se možda željeli priključiti bankovnoj uniji,

647
01:03:29,840 --> 01:03:34,600
 odnosno ući o mehanizam bliske suradnje, treba će pronaći nekakav substitut.

648
01:03:34,600 --> 01:03:39,100
 Još uvijek nije jasno koji bi taj substitut bio i koliki bi bio njegov kapacitet.

649
01:03:39,100 --> 01:03:49,460
 Također, mi ne bi imali ulazak u bankovnu uniju, ne bi nam donio i mogućnost pristupanju

650
01:03:49,460 --> 01:03:54,400
 nekakvim izvarednim kreditima za likvidnost Europske središće banke, što je bitno,

651
01:03:54,400 --> 01:03:58,980
 pogotovo bitno za visoke euroziranu zemlju, kao što je Hrvatska u kojoj su depoziti

652
01:03:58,980 --> 01:04:03,100
 preteže to u strane valuti. Neko će reći, to nije promjena u odnosu na sadašnje stanje.

653
01:04:03,100 --> 01:04:07,720
 Međutim, činjenica je da bi se ulazkom u mehanizam bliske suradnje

654
01:04:07,720 --> 01:04:18,200
 transferirala supervizija, transferirala bi se ovlasti za sanaciju banaka na centar,

655
01:04:18,200 --> 01:04:26,000
 na Frankfurt i na Brisel, a mi bi dalje bili odgovorni kao zajmodavac u krajnjoj nužni.

656
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:30,360
 Znači, Lander of the Last Resort Function bi dalje ostao u Zagrebu.

657
01:04:30,360 --> 01:04:36,320
 Znači, za nekakve potencijalne poteze koje bi mogli izazvati nestabilnost u Hrvatskoj

658
01:04:36,320 --> 01:04:40,420
 mi bi morali biti pripravni i dijelovati kao zajmodavac.

659
01:04:40,420 --> 01:04:44,660
 Znači, problem je razdvajanje ovlasti i odgovornosti.

660
01:04:44,660 --> 01:04:51,480
 Odgovornost bi ostala i dalje u Zagrebu, a ovlasti bi otišle negdje dalje.

661
01:04:51,480 --> 01:04:58,020
 Znači, nama bi bilo puno lakše donijeti odluku kad bi i odgovornost išla zajedno u paketu,

662
01:04:58,100 --> 01:05:00,260
 saselila zajedno u paketu sa ovlastima.

663
01:05:00,260 --> 01:05:12,860
 Slično je i sa naciju. Znači, u ovom među razdoblju, dok se još nije mutualizacija,

664
01:05:12,860 --> 01:05:16,540
 odnosno dok nije mutualizacija provedena u potpunoj mjeri,

665
01:05:16,540 --> 01:05:22,000
 još uvijek se jedan znatan dio troškova može osnositi na nacionalnoj razliji.

666
01:05:26,900 --> 01:05:36,080
 Također, još uvijek ne znamo kako će Europska srediča banka funkcionirati

667
01:05:36,080 --> 01:05:42,000
 kao jedan međusloj u arhitekturi za voženje makroprudencijalne politike.

668
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:45,260
 Znači, sada makroprudencijalna politika je decentralizirana.

669
01:05:45,260 --> 01:05:51,560
 U Europskoj Uniji postoji Europski odbor za sustavne rizike, SRB,

670
01:05:51,560 --> 01:05:57,340
 koji na neki način koordinira, može makroprudencijalne politike,

671
01:05:57,340 --> 01:06:01,720
 zemalja članica, može potaknuti pojedine zemlje članice na djelovanje.

672
01:06:01,720 --> 01:06:04,060
 Isto vremeno može djelovati kao barijera.

673
01:06:04,220 --> 01:06:07,460
 Ako vi morate uvjeriti Europski odbor za sustavne rizike,

674
01:06:07,460 --> 01:06:12,360
 da su neke mjere nužne i neophodne, možda ćete čekati sa aktiviranjem tih mjera.

675
01:06:12,360 --> 01:06:17,800
 Nećete ih poduzeti prvi put kad pomislite da se rizici kumuliraju u vašem financijskom sustavu.

676
01:06:19,540 --> 01:06:23,140
 U vlasku u mehanizam bliske suradnje dobijate još i Europsku središu banku

677
01:06:23,140 --> 01:06:29,180
 kao jedan dodatni međusloj koji morate uvjeriti u opravdanost svojih makroprudencijalnih politika.

678
01:06:29,180 --> 01:06:33,180
 Znači, Europska središa banka može također prigovarati nekim politikama,

679
01:06:33,180 --> 01:06:35,620
 što ne može ako ostanete izvan Bankovne unije.

680
01:06:35,620 --> 01:06:42,580
 U pogledu institucionalne kapacitete Europske središa banka,

681
01:06:42,580 --> 01:06:44,680
 jedinstveno sa nacijskog odbora, kažem do sada,

682
01:06:46,100 --> 01:06:49,560
 ono što, kažem, imamo dobru suradnju,

683
01:06:49,560 --> 01:06:54,000
 međutim, postoji nedostatak, određenje nedostatak iskustva.

684
01:06:54,000 --> 01:07:00,020
 Nešto što je posebno bitno za Hrvatsku je bojazan da subsidijari

685
01:07:00,020 --> 01:07:02,800
 u malim zemljama članicama mogu proći ispod radara.

686
01:07:02,800 --> 01:07:09,380
 Znači, naše najveće banke su 1 ili 2% svojih matečnih bankovnih grupacija.

687
01:07:09,380 --> 01:07:13,500
 Moguće je da supervizor koji će djelovati iz jednog središta,

688
01:07:13,600 --> 01:07:18,220
 iz Frankfurta, neće voditi dovoljno brige o tome da su sustavne banke

689
01:07:18,220 --> 01:07:22,640
 za Hrvatsku zapravo nebitne za svoje matečne grupe.

690
01:07:22,640 --> 01:07:28,940
 Recimo, imali smo iskustvo iz pregleda kvalitete aktive banaka,

691
01:07:28,940 --> 01:07:32,060
 takozvani asset quality review, gdje su uključene,

692
01:07:32,060 --> 01:07:36,780
 u cijeli procesu bile uključene i glavne Hrvatske banke

693
01:07:36,780 --> 01:07:40,660
 kao dijelovi svojih grupacija.

694
01:07:40,660 --> 01:07:46,280
 Međutim, uzorci portfelja koji su bili izabrani u domaćim bankama

695
01:07:46,280 --> 01:07:48,340
 nisu bili reprezentativni za te banke.

696
01:07:48,340 --> 01:07:50,860
 Znači, radio se reprezentativan portfelj,

697
01:07:50,860 --> 01:07:52,720
 isključivo za cijelokupne grupacije.

698
01:07:53,240 --> 01:07:57,760
 Tako da je Hrvatska narodna banka u skladu s naputkom

699
01:07:57,760 --> 01:08:02,780
 Europske komisije provela jedan dodatni pregled kvalitete imovine.

700
01:08:02,780 --> 01:08:05,800
 Znači, nadopunila je taj asset quality review svojim vlastitim mjerama.

701
01:08:05,800 --> 01:08:08,780
 Znači, moguće je da neke rezidici u bankovnom sustavu

702
01:08:08,780 --> 01:08:12,820
 prođu nezamjećeni, isključivo zato što nisu sustavni

703
01:08:12,820 --> 01:08:15,000
 za cijelu bankovnu uniju.

704
01:08:17,000 --> 01:08:21,220
 I također, ono što je još jedna dodatna bojazan,

705
01:08:21,220 --> 01:08:26,140
 ako se najveće grupe, najveće banke u Hrvatskoj

706
01:08:26,140 --> 01:08:30,140
 uključe u jedinstveni nadzorni mehanizam,

707
01:08:30,140 --> 01:08:31,960
 u jedinstveni mehanizam sanacije,

708
01:08:31,960 --> 01:08:36,220
 oni ostaće samo manje banke koje će puniti

709
01:08:36,220 --> 01:08:40,780
 fond za osiguranje depozita i sanacijski fond.

710
01:08:40,780 --> 01:08:43,780
 Moguće je da ako samo jedan manji dio bankovnog sustava

711
01:08:43,780 --> 01:08:46,980
 puni te fondove, da će njihov kapacitet biti

712
01:08:46,980 --> 01:08:50,480
 i nedostatan onda za nošenje s nekakvim rizicima

713
01:08:50,480 --> 01:08:52,500
 koji se mogu pojaviti.

714
01:08:52,500 --> 01:08:55,340
 Tako da, to je još jedna dodatna bojazan

715
01:08:55,340 --> 01:08:59,900
 koja može odgoditi odluku o ulazku u bankovnu uniju.

716
01:08:59,900 --> 01:09:03,540
 Također, i sama činjenica, kao što je Guvener rekao,

717
01:09:03,540 --> 01:09:06,100
 nama je u interesu i tekako u interesu da bankovna unija

718
01:09:06,100 --> 01:09:09,360
 se uspostavi, da ona dobro dijeluje,

719
01:09:09,360 --> 01:09:13,280
 čak i ako mi ne budemo funkcionalno uključeni,

720
01:09:13,280 --> 01:09:14,880
 njezni funkcionalni dio.

721
01:09:15,040 --> 01:09:18,000
 Znači, sve što povećava stabilnost u zemljama

722
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:20,120
 iz kojih dolaze, na financijsku stabilnost u zemljama

723
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:23,140
 iz kojih dolaze naše majke,

724
01:09:23,140 --> 01:09:24,840
 naših najvećih banaka,

725
01:09:24,840 --> 01:09:26,180
 je i u našem interesu.

726
01:09:26,180 --> 01:09:27,900
 Tako da mi tekako podupiremo

727
01:09:27,900 --> 01:09:30,760
 dovršetak bankovne unije

728
01:09:30,760 --> 01:09:32,440
 i smatramo da je to u našem interesu.

729
01:09:33,900 --> 01:09:36,980
 Znači, da ukratko samo sažmem prezentaciju,

730
01:09:36,980 --> 01:09:40,720
 sa jedinstvenim supervizorskim mehanizom imamo kratko,

731
01:09:40,720 --> 01:09:45,660
 ali pozitivno iskustvo u okviru suradnje u kolegijima

732
01:09:45,660 --> 01:09:49,560
 i pripreme zajedničkih odluka i također u trilatoralnom suradnju

733
01:09:49,560 --> 01:09:51,460
 u okviru on-site inspekcija.

734
01:09:51,460 --> 01:09:53,360
 Znači, kad dolaze on-site inspekcija,

735
01:09:53,360 --> 01:09:55,820
 u njoj su supervizor iz Evropske stredišnje banke,

736
01:09:55,820 --> 01:09:58,820
 iz Nacionalnih stredišnje banka i HMB-a

737
01:09:58,820 --> 01:10:02,340
 i do sada nemamo zamjerki nikakvih na tu suradnju.

738
01:10:02,340 --> 01:10:05,060
 Sa jedinstvenim mehanizmom za sanaciju,

739
01:10:05,060 --> 01:10:10,980
 za sada nemamo nikakvo iskustvo stvarnog djelovanja,

740
01:10:10,980 --> 01:10:15,540
 tako da sanacijski kolegi još nisu počeli raditi,

741
01:10:15,540 --> 01:10:17,920
 a ni sanacijske planove nismo vidjeli,

742
01:10:17,920 --> 01:10:20,600
 tako da ne znamo kako će cijeli avion je na zemlji,

743
01:10:20,600 --> 01:10:22,540
 ali još ne znamo kako će se ponašati

744
01:10:22,540 --> 01:10:24,460
 kad se naže u zraku.

745
01:10:24,460 --> 01:10:26,260
 Na zemlji dobro izgleda,

746
01:10:26,260 --> 01:10:29,080
 ali ponašanje u zraku je zapravo ono što vam je bitno.

747
01:10:29,080 --> 01:10:30,460
 Također,

748
01:10:30,460 --> 01:10:32,680
 EDIS, kako smo čuli,

749
01:10:32,680 --> 01:10:33,700
 tek se definira,

750
01:10:33,700 --> 01:10:36,520
 tako da donosi modijel odluku o sudjelovanju

751
01:10:36,520 --> 01:10:38,500
 u nečemu što još uvijek nije za sada

752
01:10:38,500 --> 01:10:40,640
 izdefiniramo.

753
01:10:40,640 --> 01:10:42,320
 Znači, da sažvem naš stav,

754
01:10:42,320 --> 01:10:45,820
 mi definitivno, HMB definitivno podupire stvaranje

755
01:10:45,820 --> 01:10:47,720
 Bankovne unije,

756
01:10:47,720 --> 01:10:48,500
 međutim, način,

757
01:10:48,500 --> 01:10:51,080
 trenutna faza u njezinom dizajnu

758
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:53,080
 povećava nešto što se zove

759
01:10:53,080 --> 01:10:56,660
 opcijska vrijednost čekanja za zemlje članice izvan europodručja.

760
01:10:56,660 --> 01:11:00,920
 Znači, odgađanje odluke o ulasku u Bankovnu uniju

761
01:11:00,920 --> 01:11:01,920
 prije uvođenja eura

762
01:11:01,920 --> 01:11:05,660
 nema, po našem mišljenju, neke visoke troškove.

763
01:11:07,180 --> 01:11:11,060
 Međutim, ako donesemo odluku o priključivanju

764
01:11:11,060 --> 01:11:12,420
 i ona se pokaže pogrešnom,

765
01:11:12,420 --> 01:11:15,120
 to može rezultirati visokim troškovima za Hrvatsku.

766
01:11:15,120 --> 01:11:17,860
 Također,

767
01:11:17,860 --> 01:11:22,260
 promatramo i ocjenjujemo poticaj

768
01:11:22,260 --> 01:11:25,060
 poput pristupa zajedničkom zaštitnom mehanizmu,

769
01:11:25,060 --> 01:11:28,440
 fiskalnom ili nejakve eventualne aranžmane

770
01:11:28,440 --> 01:11:33,380
 za pružanje likvidnosti u eurima u krajnjoj nuždi

771
01:11:33,380 --> 01:11:36,440
 i takvi nejakvi mogućnost stvaranja takvih aranžmana

772
01:11:36,440 --> 01:11:37,940
 bi nas moglo potaknuti

773
01:11:37,940 --> 01:11:40,620
 prema priključivanju u Bankovnoj uniji.

774
01:11:40,620 --> 01:11:42,440
 Znači, u jednoj rečenici,

775
01:11:42,440 --> 01:11:44,040
 uvođenje eura je strateški cilj,

776
01:11:44,040 --> 01:11:46,300
 to implicira i članstvo u Bankovnoj uniji,

777
01:11:46,300 --> 01:11:50,260
 međutim, do uvođenja eura,

778
01:11:50,260 --> 01:11:52,820
 odnosno do prikladnog trenutka,

779
01:11:52,820 --> 01:11:56,240
 naš stav je da treba se držati wait and see pristupa,

780
01:11:56,240 --> 01:11:57,680
 znači, promatranja,

781
01:11:57,680 --> 01:12:01,080
 čekanja i promatranja što se zbijeva u Bankovnoj uniji.

782
01:12:01,080 --> 01:12:02,640
 Zahvaljujem se na pažnju.

783
01:12:03,380 --> 01:12:15,360
 Veliko hvala govornicima,

784
01:12:15,360 --> 01:12:18,180
 gospodinu Rotaru i viceguverneru Šošiću.

785
01:12:18,180 --> 01:12:21,020
 Sad nas čeka kratka pauza od 15-ak minuta,

786
01:12:21,020 --> 01:12:24,020
 a potom okrugli, odnosno panel,

787
01:12:24,020 --> 01:12:25,640
 na temu Bankovne unije,

788
01:12:25,640 --> 01:12:27,480
 koju će voditi gospodin Velimir Šonje.

789
01:12:27,480 --> 01:12:37,920
 Dama i gospodo,

790
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:42,220
 dobar dan, dobar dan po drugi put.

791
01:12:42,220 --> 01:12:45,480
 Nadam sam da ste se malo odmorili

792
01:12:45,480 --> 01:12:48,320
 i ponovo skupili snagu za koncentraciju na pauzi.

793
01:12:49,500 --> 01:12:51,620
 Evo, osobito mi je zadovoljstvo i čast

794
01:12:51,620 --> 01:12:55,140
 i zahvaljujem Hrvatskoj narodnoj banci i Evropskoj komisiji

795
01:12:55,140 --> 01:12:58,760
 na prilici da moderiramo krugli stol na ovu temu

796
01:12:58,760 --> 01:13:00,460
 o kojoj smo razgovarali jutros

797
01:13:00,460 --> 01:13:03,820
 sa ovako uglednim sugovornicima.

798
01:13:05,280 --> 01:13:07,080
 Mislim da ih nema potrebe posebno.

799
01:13:07,080 --> 01:13:08,920
 Pozdravljati pa samo vrlo kratko.

800
01:13:08,920 --> 01:13:10,780
 Dakle, čuli ste jutro su uvodu

801
01:13:10,780 --> 01:13:14,060
 gospodin Filip Rotter iz Evropske komisije.

802
01:13:14,060 --> 01:13:17,360
 Tu je i viceguverner Damir Odak

803
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:19,500
 zadužen za superviziju Banaka

804
01:13:19,500 --> 01:13:21,460
 i gospodin Zdenko Adrović,

805
01:13:21,460 --> 01:13:24,080
 izdušnji direktor Hrvatske udruge Banaka.

806
01:13:24,080 --> 01:13:27,100
 Dakle, tri vrlo kvalificirana sugovornika

807
01:13:27,100 --> 01:13:29,020
 za ovu temu.

808
01:13:30,520 --> 01:13:34,280
 Iako je gospodin Rotter već...

809
01:13:34,280 --> 01:13:36,060
 Do you have...

810
01:13:36,060 --> 01:13:36,400
 Sorry.

811
01:13:36,400 --> 01:13:40,680
 Ok, then I will switch to English just for you.

812
01:13:40,680 --> 01:13:41,380
 For the time being, yeah.

813
01:13:41,380 --> 01:13:42,500
 Yes, for the time being.

814
01:13:42,500 --> 01:13:42,940
 Ok.

815
01:13:42,940 --> 01:13:45,800
 So, basically, Mr. Rotter,

816
01:13:45,800 --> 01:13:48,600
 I wanted to start a discussion with you.

817
01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:51,640
 Although you already had the presentation,

818
01:13:51,640 --> 01:13:53,620
 but there's a kind of the follow-up, yeah?

819
01:13:53,620 --> 01:13:58,920
 We will divide our discussion into fragments

820
01:13:58,920 --> 01:14:01,480
 and basically the topic that was covered

821
01:14:01,480 --> 01:14:05,080
 by vice governor Sosic,

822
01:14:05,080 --> 01:14:07,280
 the perspective of the small country

823
01:14:07,280 --> 01:14:09,060
 outside the Eurozone.

824
01:14:09,060 --> 01:14:11,620
 We will reach this in the end, yeah?

825
01:14:11,620 --> 01:14:16,000
 So, first, let's try to structure the conversation

826
01:14:16,000 --> 01:14:18,060
 starting from three pillars

827
01:14:18,060 --> 01:14:20,280
 and then talking a little bit about transparency

828
01:14:20,280 --> 01:14:21,660
 and then coming to the issue

829
01:14:21,660 --> 01:14:24,840
 of whether to join or not and when.

830
01:14:26,040 --> 01:14:29,420
 And let's start with the single supervisory mechanism.

831
01:14:29,420 --> 01:14:31,760
 You already provided a lot of information

832
01:14:31,760 --> 01:14:35,220
 about functioning of the single supervisory mechanism.

833
01:14:35,220 --> 01:14:37,920
 But I think it would be very interesting

834
01:14:37,920 --> 01:14:43,180
 to hear your assessment of the developments up to now.

835
01:14:43,320 --> 01:14:46,260
 How does the Commission sees the developments

836
01:14:46,260 --> 01:14:49,440
 in the first year and a half or so?

837
01:14:49,440 --> 01:14:54,680
 Do you see that the stability of European banking system

838
01:14:54,680 --> 01:14:55,640
 has improved?

839
01:14:55,640 --> 01:14:58,600
 What are the pluses and minuses

840
01:14:58,600 --> 01:15:02,000
 of the developments that we've seen in the meantime?

841
01:15:02,000 --> 01:15:06,100
 And finally, one of the main reasons

842
01:15:06,100 --> 01:15:10,700
 was the break of the sovereign bank nexus,

843
01:15:10,700 --> 01:15:12,320
 which is twofold.

844
01:15:12,320 --> 01:15:16,660
 One is related to capital markets

845
01:15:16,660 --> 01:15:17,800
 and funding of the government

846
01:15:17,800 --> 01:15:21,920
 and another is related to how does the supervision works.

847
01:15:21,920 --> 01:15:24,000
 And we all know that one of the reasons

848
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:27,420
 was related to the fact that national politics

849
01:15:27,420 --> 01:15:31,000
 was to some extent influencing banking supervision.

850
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:33,420
 So within the overall framework,

851
01:15:33,420 --> 01:15:36,840
 how do you assess the developments of SSN up to now?

852
01:15:36,840 --> 01:15:40,460
 Yeah, thank you very much for the question.

853
01:15:42,980 --> 01:15:47,340
 Now, I think what was said before

854
01:15:47,340 --> 01:15:48,860
 is actually still true.

855
01:15:48,860 --> 01:15:50,520
 It is early days,

856
01:15:50,520 --> 01:15:53,220
 especially in terms of resolution mechanism.

857
01:15:53,220 --> 01:15:56,240
 The whole idea of bank regulation,

858
01:15:56,240 --> 01:15:58,140
 supervision and resolution

859
01:15:58,140 --> 01:16:00,320
 is of course that you have an entire system

860
01:16:00,320 --> 01:16:04,320
 where banks are supervised closely over the years

861
01:16:04,320 --> 01:16:07,800
 and you can identify possible problems over time

862
01:16:07,800 --> 01:16:10,440
 early enough to induce action.

863
01:16:11,120 --> 01:16:13,640
 and only at the very, very last stage

864
01:16:13,640 --> 01:16:15,960
 you come into this resolution stage

865
01:16:15,960 --> 01:16:18,460
 where under normal circumstances

866
01:16:18,460 --> 01:16:20,600
 you have already several years of experience

867
01:16:20,600 --> 01:16:23,180
 of what this bank has been doing,

868
01:16:23,180 --> 01:16:24,240
 what is the business model,

869
01:16:24,240 --> 01:16:25,020
 is it sustainable,

870
01:16:25,020 --> 01:16:28,480
 what is the capital situation and so on.

871
01:16:28,480 --> 01:16:31,780
 So to ask now the SRM

872
01:16:31,780 --> 01:16:36,440
 to jump into the resolution processes

873
01:16:36,440 --> 01:16:38,240
 of existing businesses

874
01:16:38,240 --> 01:16:39,900
 is extremely difficult.

875
01:16:39,900 --> 01:16:43,780
 and we have seen a couple of bank interventions

876
01:16:43,780 --> 01:16:45,300
 in the past years

877
01:16:45,300 --> 01:16:47,200
 certainly in Portugal and in Italy

878
01:16:47,200 --> 01:16:49,380
 where you could of course ask

879
01:16:49,380 --> 01:16:54,080
 what is the new framework doing for us,

880
01:16:54,080 --> 01:16:55,900
 what is the value added of this new framework

881
01:16:55,900 --> 01:16:57,980
 that we are in the process of setting up

882
01:16:57,980 --> 01:16:59,560
 and you will find that

883
01:16:59,560 --> 01:17:01,760
 this is still very much a national affair

884
01:17:01,760 --> 01:17:04,780
 and I think unfortunately for the time being

885
01:17:04,780 --> 01:17:05,660
 that's where we are.

886
01:17:05,740 --> 01:17:07,840
 we are setting the thing up.

887
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:11,220
 I think it is the right direction to go

888
01:17:11,220 --> 01:17:13,680
 because as we've said before

889
01:17:13,680 --> 01:17:16,920
 the banking union should be a European affair.

890
01:17:16,920 --> 01:17:19,480
 We don't want a European union

891
01:17:19,480 --> 01:17:23,440
 with completely national fragmented banking sectors

892
01:17:23,440 --> 01:17:26,040
 so that cannot be an viable approach

893
01:17:26,040 --> 01:17:29,320
 but unfortunately it's difficult to judge

894
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:31,520
 that you know as we have now

895
01:17:31,520 --> 01:17:34,960
 the SRM is the perfect solution to anything

896
01:17:34,960 --> 01:17:36,040
 unfortunately that is

897
01:17:36,040 --> 01:17:39,720
 not possible to say.

898
01:17:40,720 --> 01:17:41,660
 the point is

899
01:17:41,660 --> 01:17:45,400
 of the whole exercise of course

900
01:17:45,400 --> 01:17:46,400
 we need credibility

901
01:17:46,400 --> 01:17:48,260
 we need credibility in the banking sector

902
01:17:48,260 --> 01:17:50,040
 that is the major thing

903
01:17:50,040 --> 01:17:52,460
 to have a functioning financial system

904
01:17:52,460 --> 01:17:54,160
 and for that purpose

905
01:17:54,160 --> 01:17:56,480
 I think the SRM is the right approach

906
01:17:56,480 --> 01:17:58,040
 we are moving in the right direction

907
01:17:58,040 --> 01:18:00,860
 and we are reducing risks

908
01:18:00,860 --> 01:18:02,540
 and trying to share the risks

909
01:18:02,540 --> 01:18:04,660
 as much as possible over time.

910
01:18:04,660 --> 01:18:07,100
 Unfortunately beyond that

911
01:18:07,100 --> 01:18:09,140
 there's not much we can say.

912
01:18:09,140 --> 01:18:10,640
 Thank you.

913
01:18:11,440 --> 01:18:12,440
 Gospodin Odak

914
01:18:12,440 --> 01:18:16,580
 vi kao dugogodišnji iskusni bankar

915
01:18:16,580 --> 01:18:18,800
 i bankovni supervizor

916
01:18:18,800 --> 01:18:21,120
 sigurno imate jedan, da tako kažem,

917
01:18:21,120 --> 01:18:22,360
 pogled izvana na to

918
01:18:22,360 --> 01:18:24,700
 kako funkcionira SSM u ovom trenutku

919
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:26,420
 iako ste se i naravno doticali

920
01:18:26,420 --> 01:18:28,440
 sa funkcioniranjem SSM-a

921
01:18:28,440 --> 01:18:31,860
 direktno kroz AQR 2014.

922
01:18:31,860 --> 01:18:35,220
 ali zapravo i kroz nešto što traje

923
01:18:35,220 --> 01:18:36,240
 već dugi niz godina

924
01:18:36,240 --> 01:18:38,600
 a to je suradnja u on-site inspekcijama

925
01:18:38,600 --> 01:18:40,960
 kolege i supervizora itd.

926
01:18:41,220 --> 01:18:42,520
 s obzirom da je to zapravo tema

927
01:18:42,520 --> 01:18:44,340
 o kojoj se malo kod nas govori

928
01:18:44,340 --> 01:18:45,920
 i malo se toga zna

929
01:18:45,920 --> 01:18:47,380
 možda bi bilo zanimljivo čuti

930
01:18:47,380 --> 01:18:49,940
 dakle uopće kako je to iskustvo

931
01:18:49,940 --> 01:18:51,560
 kako funkcionira

932
01:18:51,560 --> 01:18:54,480
 kako ste recimo u vrijeme AQR-a

933
01:18:54,480 --> 01:18:57,240
 kako je išla taj proces suradnje

934
01:18:57,240 --> 01:19:00,580
 sa Evropskom središnjom bankom i EBOM

935
01:19:00,580 --> 01:19:04,260
 i kako uz to iskustvo danas gledate

936
01:19:04,260 --> 01:19:07,660
 izvana na funkcioniranje SSM-a.

937
01:19:09,800 --> 01:19:14,140
 Da, prvo ono što mislim da je jasno

938
01:19:14,140 --> 01:19:15,720
 iz svih prezentacija do sada

939
01:19:15,720 --> 01:19:19,560
 da mi u stvari ne gledamo izvana na taj sustav.

940
01:19:19,560 --> 01:19:23,640
 Naime, on ima niz preklapanja,

941
01:19:23,640 --> 01:19:25,680
 naše aktivnosti imaju niz preklapanja

942
01:19:25,680 --> 01:19:27,520
 i one su dobrim dijelom zajedničke.

943
01:19:28,000 --> 01:19:30,580
 U prvom redu mi opet funkcioniramo

944
01:19:30,580 --> 01:19:34,380
 kako nam je gospodin Rotter pokazao

945
01:19:34,380 --> 01:19:38,160
 po single rulebooku.

946
01:19:38,160 --> 01:19:42,200
 Znači, jedna knjiga opisuje sva pravila

947
01:19:42,200 --> 01:19:43,420
 po kojima radimo,

948
01:19:43,420 --> 01:19:46,340
 kako mi, tako i SSM-a.

949
01:19:46,340 --> 01:19:50,100
 U okviru EB-e formira se nešto se zove

950
01:19:50,100 --> 01:19:51,800
 single supervisory handbook.

951
01:19:51,800 --> 01:19:56,680
 Znači, niz pravila koje supervizori moraju primjenjivati

952
01:19:56,680 --> 01:19:59,580
 kod svog svakodnevnog rada.

953
01:19:59,580 --> 01:20:03,460
 Prema tome, polazeći od zajedničkog seta pravila,

954
01:20:04,720 --> 01:20:08,020
 Mi, ono gdje se nalazimo, što se kaže, izvana,

955
01:20:08,020 --> 01:20:10,720
 je jedino u takozvanom SREP procesu,

956
01:20:10,720 --> 01:20:14,020
 odnosno u procesu gdje razgovaramo

957
01:20:14,020 --> 01:20:17,720
 kao dva ravnopravna partnera,

958
01:20:17,720 --> 01:20:19,720
 s tim što, naravno, home supervisor,

959
01:20:19,720 --> 01:20:25,720
 odnosno onaj kod kojeg je bazirana matica,

960
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:28,800
 uvijek tu ima veću odgovornost,

961
01:20:28,800 --> 01:20:33,100
 ali isto tako, polazeći od iste metodologije,

962
01:20:33,100 --> 01:20:35,000
 mi dolazimo do zajedničkih zaključaka

963
01:20:35,000 --> 01:20:36,560
 koji se supotpisuju.

964
01:20:36,560 --> 01:20:41,780
 Znači, naši nalazi o rizičnom profilu banke

965
01:20:41,780 --> 01:20:43,960
 i naš zahtjev za kapital

966
01:20:43,960 --> 01:20:48,100
 biva prihvaćen od strane home supervisora

967
01:20:48,100 --> 01:20:50,920
 i u tom dijelu moramo reći

968
01:20:50,920 --> 01:20:54,520
 da je suradnja u koleđima u kojima se to odvija

969
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:55,660
 i prije bila dobra,

970
01:20:55,660 --> 01:21:00,560
 a da preglaskom na SSM naravno tu uvijek postoje

971
01:21:00,560 --> 01:21:03,480
 određeni potresi, određene administrativne promjene,

972
01:21:03,480 --> 01:21:08,060
 ali ne možemo reći da se na bilo koji način pokvarila.

973
01:21:08,060 --> 01:21:12,560
 Smanjivanjem broja članova koleđa

974
01:21:12,560 --> 01:21:14,460
 rasprava se pojednostavljuje

975
01:21:14,460 --> 01:21:20,140
 i vjerujemo da će u konačnici proces ići u dobrom smiju.

976
01:21:22,520 --> 01:21:27,560
 Pitanje iskustva s provođenjem Asset Quality Review-a je jedno zanimljivo pitanje,

977
01:21:27,560 --> 01:21:32,020
 jer kao što je Vedran primijetio, Asset Quality Review je bio ciljan

978
01:21:32,020 --> 01:21:35,240
 da dobije cjelovite informacije na razini grupa.

979
01:21:35,240 --> 01:21:42,360
 On nije bio ciljan da nama omogući da mi steknemo cjeloviti uvid u stanje naših banaka.

980
01:21:43,060 --> 01:21:46,280
 Međutim, to ne vidimo da je neki problem,

981
01:21:46,280 --> 01:21:51,900
 jer mi smo prvo kontinuirano dobro informirani o stanju naših banaka,

982
01:21:51,900 --> 01:21:55,560
 tako da mislimo da provođenje Asset Quality Review-a

983
01:21:55,560 --> 01:22:02,080
 nije nam otvorilo neka nova područja

984
01:22:02,080 --> 01:22:04,860
 koja bi bila recimo tako neočekivana,

985
01:22:04,860 --> 01:22:09,820
 ali smo za svaki slučaj i u suradnji s Europskom komisijom

986
01:22:09,820 --> 01:22:12,540
 uspješno dopunili Asset Quality Review,

987
01:22:12,540 --> 01:22:16,680
 tako da smo one portfelje koji su bili potrebni za verifikaciju

988
01:22:16,680 --> 01:22:20,540
 da primjerom iste metodologije neće doći do drugačijih rezultata

989
01:22:20,540 --> 01:22:23,680
 pregledali u paralelnom postupku

990
01:22:23,680 --> 01:22:27,040
 i ono što se možemo pohvaliti,

991
01:22:27,040 --> 01:22:28,820
 mislim da je to stvar za pohvalu,

992
01:22:28,820 --> 01:22:33,040
 je da smo cijelu tu vježbu odradili sa našim resursima,

993
01:22:33,040 --> 01:22:35,680
 odnosno u suradnji sa home supervisorima,

994
01:22:35,680 --> 01:22:40,500
 za razliku od većine drugih jurisdikcija,

995
01:22:40,500 --> 01:22:42,480
 nismo uzimali vanjske resurse,

996
01:22:42,480 --> 01:22:45,160
 nego smo sve sa svojim ljudima napravili,

997
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:47,740
 što je naravno imalo određenih posljedica

998
01:22:47,740 --> 01:22:51,200
 na cjelovitost supervizije sustava,

999
01:22:51,200 --> 01:22:56,480
 ali mislim da je dobro obzirom na usporedive troške u drugim jurisdikcijama.

1000
01:22:58,540 --> 01:23:00,540
 Ako može, jedno podpitanje zapravo,

1001
01:23:00,540 --> 01:23:03,820
 jer meni je ovo vrlo zanimljivo i mislim da je možda ključno pitanje.

1002
01:23:03,820 --> 01:23:07,260
 Dakle, nekako je teza išla u pravcu

1003
01:23:07,260 --> 01:23:11,700
 da ukoliko se uđe u bankarsku uniju

1004
01:23:11,700 --> 01:23:17,760
 i ako je Evropska središnja banka nadzire grupaciju,

1005
01:23:17,760 --> 01:23:21,800
 da će onda doći do, zbog definiranja uzorka portfelja kreditnog,

1006
01:23:21,800 --> 01:23:23,480
 naravno i drugih izloženosti,

1007
01:23:23,480 --> 01:23:28,080
 da će doći do zanemarivanja u nekom, da tako kažem,

1008
01:23:28,080 --> 01:23:30,380
 repu distribucije rizika grupacije,

1009
01:23:30,380 --> 01:23:34,460
 gdje se nalazi, međutim, sistemski važna lokalna banka.

1010
01:23:34,460 --> 01:23:37,960
 Ali koliko je taj strah uopće realan?

1011
01:23:37,960 --> 01:23:41,860
 Dakle, zar ipak ne postoji ta,

1012
01:23:41,860 --> 01:23:44,720
 i u bankarskoj uniji ne bi li trebala postojati

1013
01:23:44,720 --> 01:23:46,400
 takva razina suradnje između

1014
01:23:46,400 --> 01:23:50,660
 Evropske središnje banke i lokalnog supervizora

1015
01:23:50,660 --> 01:23:54,120
 koji ne nestaje, nego i dalje obavlja svoj posao,

1016
01:23:54,120 --> 01:23:58,420
 u smislu da ako je nešto sistemski važno

1017
01:23:58,420 --> 01:24:02,040
 da bude zahvaćeno pregledom na jednak način

1018
01:24:02,040 --> 01:24:04,520
 kao što je bilo zahvaćeno i ranije.

1019
01:24:04,520 --> 01:24:08,200
 Ili ipak ova bojazan stoji po vašem mišljenju?

1020
01:24:08,200 --> 01:24:13,640
 Dakle, ono što je Vedran rekao,

1021
01:24:13,640 --> 01:24:16,740
 Vedran je rekao temeljem naših iskustava

1022
01:24:16,740 --> 01:24:20,100
 i zajedničkih razmišljanja na tu temu.

1023
01:24:20,100 --> 01:24:25,240
 U svakom slučaju, ono što moramo biti svjesni

1024
01:24:25,240 --> 01:24:28,800
 je da svako uvijek primarno rješava svoj problem.

1025
01:24:28,800 --> 01:24:34,400
 Ondje gdje predstavljaš jedan ili dva posto sustava,

1026
01:24:34,400 --> 01:24:36,180
 ti si jedan ili dva posto.

1027
01:24:36,580 --> 01:24:39,140
 Znači, suštinski si, što se kaže, expendable.

1028
01:24:39,140 --> 01:24:47,600
 I naravno, mi ćemo biti, i kad se uključimo u bankarsku uniju,

1029
01:24:47,600 --> 01:24:50,180
 mi ćemo biti dio joint supervisory teama,

1030
01:24:50,180 --> 01:24:54,100
 ali joint supervisory team radi under auspices,

1031
01:24:54,100 --> 01:24:56,320
 znači pod nadzorom ECB-a.

1032
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:59,340
 On nije ravnopravni sugovornik ECB-u.

1033
01:24:59,340 --> 01:25:03,240
 Za razliku od koleđa, gdje smo mi ravnopravni sugovornik

1034
01:25:03,240 --> 01:25:06,440
 i gdje mi na kraju se ECB-om potpisujemo papir

1035
01:25:06,440 --> 01:25:09,500
 u kojem nećemo potpisati dok nismo s njim zadovoljni.

1036
01:25:09,500 --> 01:25:14,380
 Naravno, sigurni smo da kroz joint supervisory team

1037
01:25:14,380 --> 01:25:17,120
 će se te stvari moći adresirati.

1038
01:25:17,120 --> 01:25:19,460
 Sigurni smo da će ECB voditi računa

1039
01:25:19,460 --> 01:25:22,340
 i o financijskoj stabilnosti Republike Hrvatske,

1040
01:25:22,340 --> 01:25:26,280
 ali kako su svi sugovornici rekli,

1041
01:25:26,280 --> 01:25:29,840
 ovaj proces je još u relativno ranoj fazi.

1042
01:25:29,840 --> 01:25:36,620
 Prema tome, najvjerovatnije taj slučaj se ne bi dogodio,

1043
01:25:36,620 --> 01:25:40,380
 odnosno mi bi ga sa odgovarajućim kontraaktivnostima

1044
01:25:40,380 --> 01:25:43,920
 mogli kompenzirati, ali to je najvjerovatnije.

1045
01:25:43,920 --> 01:25:47,880
 Hvala lijepo na vrlo informativnom odgovoru

1046
01:25:47,880 --> 01:25:51,340
 i vjerojatno je pravi trenutak da pitamo gospodina Adrovića

1047
01:25:51,340 --> 01:25:54,600
 s obzirom da evo sad već postoji iskustvo

1048
01:25:54,600 --> 01:25:57,300
 od IQR-a je prošlo godinu i po,

1049
01:25:57,300 --> 01:25:59,840
 umeđu vremenu su bila grupacija,

1050
01:25:59,840 --> 01:26:03,040
 nekoliko naših vodećih grupacija je zapravo

1051
01:26:03,040 --> 01:26:06,240
 u sustavu banaka koje su pod izravnom ingerencijom ECB-a.

1052
01:26:06,240 --> 01:26:10,440
 Kakve su iskustva banaka i kako one gledaju

1053
01:26:10,440 --> 01:26:14,880
 na ovih prvih godinu i po razvoja SSM-a?

1054
01:26:14,880 --> 01:26:18,140
 Hvala na pitanju.

1055
01:26:19,580 --> 01:26:22,840
 Kao što ste svi rekli zapravo postoji iskustvo i ono nije malo

1056
01:26:22,840 --> 01:26:28,620
 u radu jednog dijela hrvatskih banaka sa ECB-om i za vrijeme

1057
01:26:28,620 --> 01:26:33,840
 asset quality review-a mogu samo reći da su sve banke imale i imaju vrlo pozitivno iskustvo

1058
01:26:33,840 --> 01:26:43,280
 i dobro je. Ono gdje mi vidimo zapravo problem u ovom trenutku za jedan dio naših banaka,

1059
01:26:43,280 --> 01:26:48,000
 a naša bankarska industrija je, nažalost, heterogena.

1060
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:55,940
 Na jednoj strani imamo, recimo to vrlo grubo, jednu trećinu banaka brojčano koje su u stranom vlasništu

1061
01:26:55,940 --> 01:26:59,960
 i otprilike dvije trećine banaka koje su, recimo, u nekom domaćem vlasništu,

1062
01:26:59,960 --> 01:27:08,800
 pri čemu trećina banaka u stranom vlasništu ima, recimo, negdje oko 80-85% kapitala i imovine.

1063
01:27:09,580 --> 01:27:18,800
 Problem je u istovremenoj primjeni i lokalnih propisa i IFRS-a i moram priznati da to u značajnom mjeri

1064
01:27:18,800 --> 01:27:23,500
 angažira ljudske kapacitete i IT resources.

1065
01:27:23,500 --> 01:27:30,300
 I to ne predstavlja beznačajan trošak za banke, dakle to je double reporting kojim se bavimo

1066
01:27:30,300 --> 01:27:38,680
 i tu bi sasvim sigurno dio bankarske industrije imao koristi u ulazku u Bankarsku uniju

1067
01:27:38,680 --> 01:27:47,500
 kada bi se prekinula primjena lokalnih propisa i time oslobodio jedan dio ljudskih i IT kapaciteta.

1068
01:27:47,500 --> 01:27:51,520
 Hvala lijepo.

1069
01:27:51,520 --> 01:27:57,300
 Drugim riječima, ispričatam ako nešto krivo reinterpretiram,

1070
01:27:59,300 --> 01:28:05,020
 kada bi se primjenjivali isti regulator na pravila, onda zapravo i ne bi bilo bitno da li ulazimo ili ne?

1071
01:28:05,020 --> 01:28:06,840
 Jesam dobro shvatio?

1072
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:09,280
 Pa onda bi bilo bitno lakše, da.

1073
01:28:09,280 --> 01:28:11,600
 Dobro. Hvala.

1074
01:28:11,600 --> 01:28:15,220
 Gospodine Roter, funkcionira sad sve, evo.

1075
01:28:15,220 --> 01:28:19,900
 Predlažem da kratko se dotaknemo o osiguranja depozita,

1076
01:28:19,900 --> 01:28:26,680
 naime čuli smo sustav još u izgradnji, to je onaj gore treći kat na kojem još građevinari rade,

1077
01:28:26,680 --> 01:28:31,460
 kao što nam je vice guverner objasnio sa graditeljskom metaforom.

1078
01:28:31,460 --> 01:28:36,300
 Mene je zapravo jedna stvar malo zagolicala u vašoj prezentaciji o EDIS-u,

1079
01:28:36,300 --> 01:28:44,900
 a to je najava da diferencirane premije u objedinjenom sustavu su zamišljene tek nakon tri godine,

1080
01:28:44,900 --> 01:28:46,180
 ako sam dobro shvatio.

1081
01:28:46,280 --> 01:28:49,420
 Evo tako, pisala je na vašoj prezentaciji tri godine kasnije.

1082
01:28:49,420 --> 01:28:51,940
 Pa me to malo zbunilo,

1083
01:28:51,940 --> 01:28:56,640
 s obzirom da sve zemlje pojedinačno sada, po postojećoj direktivi,

1084
01:28:56,640 --> 01:29:01,280
 moraju početi primjenjivati diferencijaciju premija prema riziku.

1085
01:29:01,960 --> 01:29:08,780
 Ako sam vas dobro razumio, zašto se onda tek nakon tri godine u objedinjenom sustavu,

1086
01:29:08,780 --> 01:29:10,420
 u eventualnom budućem EDIS-u,

1087
01:29:10,420 --> 01:29:14,440
 predviđa ta neka prijelazna faza, ponovo povratak na jedinstvenu,

1088
01:29:14,440 --> 01:29:19,660
 pa tek onda na premiranje prema riziku i bilo koje drugo zapažanje u vezi EDISA,

1089
01:29:19,660 --> 01:29:21,640
 ako želite iskomunicirati.

1090
01:29:24,640 --> 01:29:30,740
 Ja, maybe there's something to make a bit clearer than I did in my presentation.

1091
01:29:30,740 --> 01:29:36,580
 There's these three stages of the EDIS which we foresee in the proposal,

1092
01:29:36,580 --> 01:29:39,760
 from the reinsurance stage, the coinsurance stage,

1093
01:29:39,760 --> 01:29:42,560
 and then the fully developed stage.

1094
01:29:42,560 --> 01:29:47,540
 And the reinsurance stage, the first stage of this EDIS in 2017-2019,

1095
01:29:47,540 --> 01:29:51,240
 is still very much a national approach.

1096
01:29:51,240 --> 01:29:56,200
 There is the EDIS, but it only jumps in once national resources have been exhausted,

1097
01:29:56,200 --> 01:30:01,680
 and the whole setup is very much one of national compartments.

1098
01:30:01,680 --> 01:30:07,880
 And in that regard, also the contributions are oriented very much on national guidelines.

1099
01:30:07,880 --> 01:30:11,560
 So, as you correctly observed, under the DGSD,

1100
01:30:11,560 --> 01:30:20,860
 already now the national guarantee schemes are supposed to implement risk-based contribution rates,

1101
01:30:21,240 --> 01:30:24,400
 and those would continue in the first stage.

1102
01:30:24,400 --> 01:30:32,980
 So, national schemes would set their contribution rates according to their own national parameters.

1103
01:30:32,980 --> 01:30:35,440
 Of course, there should be some harmonization,

1104
01:30:35,440 --> 01:30:40,460
 but only once we move to the second so-called coinsurance stage,

1105
01:30:40,460 --> 01:30:44,020
 then the board would take over the singular resolution board,

1106
01:30:44,020 --> 01:30:47,280
 which would apparently administer the EDIS,

1107
01:30:47,280 --> 01:30:54,280
 would take over the decision on how the contributions are set up.

1108
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:56,900
 And they would take into account risk parameters,

1109
01:30:56,900 --> 01:31:01,600
 you know, loss absorption, liquidity, solvency, funding, non-performing loans,

1110
01:31:01,600 --> 01:31:05,420
 all these things that we well know.

1111
01:31:06,240 --> 01:31:11,960
 And then at that stage, there was the discretion of the national schemes would be much more limited.

1112
01:31:11,960 --> 01:31:17,100
 There could be still some discretion because bank systems are very much a national affair,

1113
01:31:17,100 --> 01:31:19,600
 and there's no one-size-fits-all for everybody.

1114
01:31:19,600 --> 01:31:22,300
 But it would be mostly harmonized,

1115
01:31:22,300 --> 01:31:25,020
 and the share of national discretion would be less,

1116
01:31:25,020 --> 01:31:28,220
 whereas in the first stage, the reinsurance stage,

1117
01:31:28,220 --> 01:31:33,160
 it would be much more a national approach with some degree of harmonization.

1118
01:31:33,160 --> 01:31:36,380
 And so the weights between national and harmonized approach

1119
01:31:36,380 --> 01:31:38,460
 kind of shift between these two phases.

1120
01:31:38,460 --> 01:31:40,020
 Thank you.

1121
01:31:40,020 --> 01:31:45,180
 Gospodine Odak, mi se natragu usklađivanja sa direktivom,

1122
01:31:45,180 --> 01:31:47,900
 koliko sam informiran od ove godine,

1123
01:31:47,900 --> 01:31:51,780
 krećemo sa primjenom diferenciranih premija,

1124
01:31:51,780 --> 01:31:56,960
 iako imamo nezavisnu agenciju koja brine o tome,

1125
01:31:56,960 --> 01:31:58,100
 direktorica je ovdje,

1126
01:31:58,100 --> 01:32:01,120
 HNB ima ulogu u tom procesu,

1127
01:32:01,120 --> 01:32:03,180
 jel' tako, pa ako možete vrlo kratko objasniti

1128
01:32:03,180 --> 01:32:06,900
 koja je uloga HNB-a u procesu uvođenja diferenciranih premija

1129
01:32:06,900 --> 01:32:11,340
 i vaš pogled na efekte diferenciranja.

1130
01:32:11,340 --> 01:32:13,760
 Naime, kod uvođenja diferenciranja se uvijek postavljao pitanje,

1131
01:32:13,760 --> 01:32:17,140
 s jedne strane je jako dobro da kroz diferenciranje

1132
01:32:17,140 --> 01:32:20,540
 eliminiramo moralni hazard i zapravo doprinesemo stabilnost,

1133
01:32:20,540 --> 01:32:26,180
 s druge strane je strah da to može pogurati neke loše banke brže u probleme.

1134
01:32:26,300 --> 01:32:28,000
 O, kako gledate na taj problem?

1135
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:32,260
 Naravno, kako ste rekli,

1136
01:32:32,260 --> 01:32:37,640
 to je definiranje premija je primarno odgovornost DAB-a,

1137
01:32:37,640 --> 01:32:40,140
 znači DAB će tu sačiniti prijedlog,

1138
01:32:40,140 --> 01:32:42,340
 polazeći od stanja na tržištu,

1139
01:32:42,580 --> 01:32:45,580
 i sigurni smo da će to učiniti odgovorno.

1140
01:32:45,580 --> 01:32:51,620
 Znači da će uzeti u obzir oba dvije činjenice koje ste rekli kod kalibracije,

1141
01:32:51,620 --> 01:32:59,500
 jer sigurno nikome nije u interesu da napravimo stvar tako da ona loše funkcionira,

1142
01:32:59,500 --> 01:33:06,400
 odnosno da izazove ono što bi trebala spijećiti, odnosno amortizirati.

1143
01:33:06,960 --> 01:33:11,100
 Tako da je to nešto o čemu će sigurno sam DAB voditi računa,

1144
01:33:11,100 --> 01:33:14,780
 međutim DAB će tu biti u komunikaciji sa Hrvatskom narodnom bankom,

1145
01:33:14,780 --> 01:33:16,420
 koja ima svoju formalnu ulogu,

1146
01:33:16,420 --> 01:33:22,960
 koja će pregledati sve to i u slučaju da primijeti nešto što nam se čini problematično,

1147
01:33:22,960 --> 01:33:29,160
 siguran sam da ćemo s DABom vrlo lako naći zajednički jezik i tu stvar riješiti.

1148
01:33:29,160 --> 01:33:33,700
 Tako da ne očekujem da bi na tom području moglo biti bitnih problema.

1149
01:33:33,700 --> 01:33:43,020
 Prije će biti ovo prvo što ste rekli, znači da ta diferencijacija inicijalno neće moći biti prežestoka,

1150
01:33:43,020 --> 01:33:48,600
 ali polazeći od nekih polaznih točaka,

1151
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:54,840
 sigurno je isto tako da će i supervizija i DAB morati u nekakvom strateškim koracima

1152
01:33:54,840 --> 01:34:03,420
 prema naprijed, razmisliti kako da se ta diferencijacija napredvidiv i unaprijed opisani način ojača

1153
01:34:03,420 --> 01:34:08,280
 i da se pitanje moralnog hazarda na ispravan način adresira.

1154
01:34:08,280 --> 01:34:15,240
 Gospodine Adrović, banke su nekako, barem udruga banaka,

1155
01:34:15,240 --> 01:34:20,320
 koliko se sjećam uvijek pozitivno gledala na diferencijaciju premire,

1156
01:34:20,320 --> 01:34:26,700
 je li to još uvijek stav udruge i kako općenito gledate na očekivane efekte te mjere?

1157
01:34:26,700 --> 01:34:35,060
 Diferencirana premija je sasvim sigurno civilizacijska dostignuća i nema nekake ozbiljne alternative.

1158
01:34:35,060 --> 01:34:43,180
 Banke već imaju iskustva u primjeri diferencirane premije prošle godine kada je počela uplata u sanacijski fond,

1159
01:34:43,180 --> 01:34:48,300
 a evo očekujemo, naravno to je bio jedan manji iznos, koliko se ja sjećam,

1160
01:34:48,300 --> 01:34:51,640
 lam sam koji je uplećen je 170 i nešto miliona kuna,

1161
01:34:51,640 --> 01:34:58,620
 ali kad se počne primjenivati diferencijana premija i na uplate u fond osiguranja depozita,

1162
01:34:58,620 --> 01:35:01,420
 to će onda biti sasvim sigurno još ozbiljnija igra.

1163
01:35:01,420 --> 01:35:05,920
 Mislim da možemo očekivati da će uprave banaka biti zainteresirane,

1164
01:35:06,920 --> 01:35:12,080
 svoja ponašanja početi prilagođavati i smanjivati svoj risk profil,

1165
01:35:12,080 --> 01:35:17,320
 jer su to značajni troškovi i sasvim sigurno da banka sa nižim rizičnim profilom

1166
01:35:17,320 --> 01:35:19,620
 može uštediti dosta novaca.

1167
01:35:19,620 --> 01:35:22,020
 I to su naše očekivanja za budućnost.

1168
01:35:22,020 --> 01:35:26,620
 Hvala lijepo, evo spomenuli ste uplate u sanacijski fond,

1169
01:35:26,620 --> 01:35:29,880
 što nas dovodi zapravo do našeg trećeg pitanja,

1170
01:35:29,880 --> 01:35:37,540
 a to je u širem smislu tema sanacija i oporavka u kontekstu SRB-a i SRF-a.

1171
01:35:37,540 --> 01:35:47,720
 Gospodine Rotter, cijeli mehanizam koji počiva zapravo na BRRD-u

1172
01:35:47,720 --> 01:35:52,260
 je zapravo dizajniran da, kao što smo rekli na početku,

1173
01:35:52,260 --> 01:35:55,460
 omekša ili razbije banks over in nexus.

1174
01:35:55,460 --> 01:36:02,780
 Tu je osobito važan i očekivani mehanizam sanacija,

1175
01:36:02,780 --> 01:36:07,640
 dakle, bail-in, pitanje na koji način se primjenjuje bail-in itd.,

1176
01:36:07,640 --> 01:36:11,760
 ali je isto tako važan i segment koji ste vi spomenuli,

1177
01:36:11,760 --> 01:36:12,960
 a to je fiscal backstop.

1178
01:36:15,800 --> 01:36:19,000
 Gospodin Šošić, vice guvernerija, u svojoj prezentaciji

1179
01:36:19,000 --> 01:36:23,340
 govorio dosta optimistično u kontekstu fiscal backstopa,

1180
01:36:23,340 --> 01:36:29,080
 naglasiši da SM ima zapravo tu ulogu za zemlje eurozone,

1181
01:36:29,080 --> 01:36:32,160
 što znači da za ove izvane eurozone nema,

1182
01:36:32,160 --> 01:36:36,260
 a vi ste s druge strane rekli, ako sam dobro uočio tu nijansu razlike,

1183
01:36:36,260 --> 01:36:40,260
 da se o fiscal backstopu zapravo tek treba razgovarati

1184
01:36:40,260 --> 01:36:43,260
 i da je to tema koja je na stolu i koja je otvorena.

1185
01:36:43,260 --> 01:36:46,500
 Pa ako možete malo dalje dublje prokomentirati ovu temu

1186
01:36:46,500 --> 01:36:48,820
 s naglaskom na fiscal backstop problem.

1187
01:36:48,820 --> 01:36:58,800
 That's of course a fairly difficult question.

1188
01:36:58,800 --> 01:37:00,640
 It's clear.

1189
01:37:00,640 --> 01:37:05,300
 This is a political issue on the fiscal backstop

1190
01:37:05,300 --> 01:37:11,200
 and the major question is,

1191
01:37:11,200 --> 01:37:14,760
 I think everybody agrees that there should be a common backstop,

1192
01:37:14,760 --> 01:37:18,640
 is the question about sequencing.

1193
01:37:18,640 --> 01:37:21,280
 The whole approach as we have heard this morning

1194
01:37:21,280 --> 01:37:25,960
 comes really from the very broad area.

1195
01:37:25,960 --> 01:37:27,380
 We want to deepen EMU.

1196
01:37:27,380 --> 01:37:29,740
 We want to make EMU more competitive.

1197
01:37:29,740 --> 01:37:31,460
 if we want to make it more stable

1198
01:37:31,460 --> 01:37:34,680
 to enforce growth potential.

1199
01:37:34,680 --> 01:37:38,440
 Then you go to the financial market aspect

1200
01:37:38,440 --> 01:37:42,200
 and then we say we want to make financial markets more stable.

1201
01:37:42,200 --> 01:37:44,560
 We're pushing for capital markets union

1202
01:37:44,560 --> 01:37:46,620
 to push these issues.

1203
01:37:47,300 --> 01:37:50,180
 We are sorry to say that we are not

1204
01:37:50,180 --> 01:37:56,660
 or we are promoting EMU

1205
01:37:56,660 --> 01:37:58,520
 where the banking sector does not play

1206
01:37:58,520 --> 01:38:01,900
 the sole single dominant role in the economy.

1207
01:38:01,900 --> 01:38:04,440
 So we are certainly hoping that

1208
01:38:04,440 --> 01:38:07,920
 other forms of financing outside bank credit

1209
01:38:07,920 --> 01:38:11,940
 would be more readily used and accessible

1210
01:38:11,940 --> 01:38:14,740
 certainly for small and medium-sized enterprises.

1211
01:38:14,740 --> 01:38:17,640
 So all these issues move into the direction

1212
01:38:17,640 --> 01:38:23,440
 to reduce the risk inherent in the banking system

1213
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:25,280
 as we have seen in the past.

1214
01:38:25,280 --> 01:38:27,440
 Now in the banking sector itself,

1215
01:38:27,440 --> 01:38:31,280
 we move on with tighter regulation

1216
01:38:31,280 --> 01:38:34,340
 and certainly capital ratios have moved up a lot

1217
01:38:34,340 --> 01:38:35,840
 and much has been done.

1218
01:38:35,840 --> 01:38:38,620
 We are moving towards risk reduction

1219
01:38:38,620 --> 01:38:40,760
 as we have discussed before

1220
01:38:40,760 --> 01:38:45,440
 talking about the risk weighting of sovereign exposure.

1221
01:38:45,440 --> 01:38:47,320
 And then only at the very end

1222
01:38:47,320 --> 01:38:49,640
 of this very wide and long process

1223
01:38:49,640 --> 01:38:53,900
 we talk about this common backstop issue.

1224
01:38:53,900 --> 01:38:56,700
 In the end, I think we are,

1225
01:38:56,700 --> 01:39:02,540
 we agree that it's difficult to imagine

1226
01:39:02,540 --> 01:39:04,560
 a banking union where not at the end

1227
01:39:04,560 --> 01:39:09,500
 there is some final backstop behind it.

1228
01:39:09,500 --> 01:39:11,780
 And given the setup in EMU

1229
01:39:11,780 --> 01:39:13,560
 where we have the independent central bank

1230
01:39:13,560 --> 01:39:17,040
 which is not acting as an end of last resort,

1231
01:39:17,040 --> 01:39:18,580
 certainly at least not for governments,

1232
01:39:18,580 --> 01:39:21,760
 we need a mechanism to think about.

1233
01:39:21,760 --> 01:39:23,580
 You know, how can that be set up

1234
01:39:23,580 --> 01:39:25,180
 in this very special situation

1235
01:39:25,180 --> 01:39:26,520
 that is different from the US,

1236
01:39:26,520 --> 01:39:29,480
 it's different from any other national state

1237
01:39:29,480 --> 01:39:31,080
 which has its own currency to manage

1238
01:39:31,080 --> 01:39:36,160
 in a still conglomerate of member states.

1239
01:39:36,160 --> 01:39:38,040
 You need some mechanism

1240
01:39:38,040 --> 01:39:39,880
 which is capable of performing

1241
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:42,300
 this function which is economically justified

1242
01:39:42,300 --> 01:39:45,000
 but without, you know,

1243
01:39:45,000 --> 01:39:46,580
 without a political setup

1244
01:39:46,580 --> 01:39:48,500
 that would usually go along with it

1245
01:39:48,500 --> 01:39:51,120
 in typical systems at the national level.

1246
01:39:51,120 --> 01:39:52,840
 So in the end,

1247
01:39:52,840 --> 01:39:54,620
 there has to be something

1248
01:39:54,620 --> 01:39:56,660
 whether you formalize it ex ante

1249
01:39:56,660 --> 01:39:58,000
 as we are trying to do now

1250
01:39:58,000 --> 01:39:58,840
 with the common backstop

1251
01:39:58,840 --> 01:40:01,120
 or whether you wait and do nothing

1252
01:40:01,120 --> 01:40:02,920
 and then only when, you know,

1253
01:40:02,920 --> 01:40:03,980
 worst comes to worst

1254
01:40:03,980 --> 01:40:05,920
 we find out we need something

1255
01:40:05,920 --> 01:40:07,160
 and then you scramble

1256
01:40:07,160 --> 01:40:09,180
 and set up something over the weekend

1257
01:40:09,180 --> 01:40:10,700
 which is probably the alternative.

1258
01:40:10,700 --> 01:40:12,460
 I think we should rather go

1259
01:40:12,460 --> 01:40:13,740
 for this first approach

1260
01:40:13,740 --> 01:40:17,340
 and push for a framework arrangement

1261
01:40:17,340 --> 01:40:19,180
 at least that gives people,

1262
01:40:19,180 --> 01:40:21,660
 you know, we are talking about credibility,

1263
01:40:21,660 --> 01:40:23,820
 gives people the assurance

1264
01:40:23,820 --> 01:40:25,100
 that whatever happens,

1265
01:40:25,480 --> 01:40:26,520
 you know, their bank deposits

1266
01:40:26,520 --> 01:40:28,820
 are insured up to a certain point

1267
01:40:28,820 --> 01:40:30,300
 and there is no, you know,

1268
01:40:30,300 --> 01:40:31,440
 terrific loss.

1269
01:40:31,440 --> 01:40:32,940
 Certainly some people will lose

1270
01:40:32,940 --> 01:40:34,340
 but those people who will lose

1271
01:40:34,340 --> 01:40:36,160
 should know ex ante

1272
01:40:36,160 --> 01:40:37,780
 that they bought instruments

1273
01:40:37,780 --> 01:40:38,980
 which are exposed to risk

1274
01:40:38,980 --> 01:40:39,940
 and then it's only fair

1275
01:40:39,940 --> 01:40:41,580
 that they should also carry some risk

1276
01:40:41,580 --> 01:40:43,860
 but those people who are invested

1277
01:40:43,860 --> 01:40:44,380
 in instruments

1278
01:40:44,380 --> 01:40:45,120
 which are, you know,

1279
01:40:45,120 --> 01:40:46,220
 supposedly risk-free

1280
01:40:46,220 --> 01:40:47,220
 should be assured

1281
01:40:47,220 --> 01:40:49,480
 that this holds under all circumstances.

1282
01:40:51,680 --> 01:40:52,440
 Thank you.

1283
01:40:52,440 --> 01:40:55,580
 Could we maybe speculate

1284
01:40:55,580 --> 01:40:58,460
 about time

1285
01:40:58,460 --> 01:41:00,740
 when the issue of ex ante

1286
01:41:00,740 --> 01:41:01,960
 fiscal backstop

1287
01:41:01,960 --> 01:41:03,580
 might be discussed

1288
01:41:03,580 --> 01:41:04,760
 in the EU

1289
01:41:04,760 --> 01:41:05,980
 at the political level

1290
01:41:05,980 --> 01:41:07,540
 or it's too early

1291
01:41:07,540 --> 01:41:08,460
 for this question?

1292
01:41:08,460 --> 01:41:09,680
 Yeah.

1293
01:41:09,680 --> 01:41:11,720
 Well, it's always good to speculate.

1294
01:41:13,640 --> 01:41:15,760
 I would think

1295
01:41:15,760 --> 01:41:17,560
 this should happen next year.

1296
01:41:17,560 --> 01:41:19,300
 Next year we come up

1297
01:41:19,300 --> 01:41:20,000
 with a white paper

1298
01:41:20,000 --> 01:41:21,660
 that was addressed already

1299
01:41:21,660 --> 01:41:22,280
 with, you know,

1300
01:41:22,280 --> 01:41:23,340
 the further ideas

1301
01:41:23,340 --> 01:41:24,580
 how to deepen EMU.

1302
01:41:24,580 --> 01:41:25,640
 We are in the

1303
01:41:25,640 --> 01:41:27,080
 what we call the first stage

1304
01:41:27,080 --> 01:41:28,860
 under the five presidents report.

1305
01:41:28,860 --> 01:41:29,600
 So we have done

1306
01:41:29,600 --> 01:41:30,300
 a couple of things

1307
01:41:30,300 --> 01:41:31,660
 National Competitiveness Board,

1308
01:41:31,660 --> 01:41:34,060
 Advisory European Fiscal Board.

1309
01:41:34,060 --> 01:41:34,420
 You know,

1310
01:41:34,420 --> 01:41:35,180
 there are some processes

1311
01:41:35,180 --> 01:41:35,820
 that have been launched

1312
01:41:35,820 --> 01:41:36,900
 certainly banking union

1313
01:41:36,900 --> 01:41:38,340
 many things have been done.

1314
01:41:38,820 --> 01:41:40,020
 So next year is

1315
01:41:40,020 --> 01:41:41,020
 under the timeline

1316
01:41:41,020 --> 01:41:41,640
 that was given

1317
01:41:41,640 --> 01:41:42,760
 by the five presidents report

1318
01:41:42,760 --> 01:41:43,920
 the time to think

1319
01:41:43,920 --> 01:41:45,200
 about these concrete steps

1320
01:41:45,200 --> 01:41:45,820
 and certainly

1321
01:41:45,820 --> 01:41:47,740
 these steps involve

1322
01:41:47,740 --> 01:41:48,680
 mutualization,

1323
01:41:48,680 --> 01:41:51,320
 common arrangements,

1324
01:41:51,320 --> 01:41:52,500
 common fiscal arrangements

1325
01:41:52,500 --> 01:41:53,780
 that will cost money

1326
01:41:53,780 --> 01:41:54,740
 of all participants.

1327
01:41:54,740 --> 01:41:56,160
 That should be clear

1328
01:41:56,160 --> 01:41:57,400
 and that should be openly discussed.

1329
01:41:57,400 --> 01:41:59,460
 Thank you.

1330
01:42:00,280 --> 01:42:01,340
 Gospodine Odak,

1331
01:42:01,340 --> 01:42:02,400
 ova tema

1332
01:42:02,400 --> 01:42:04,080
 oporavka i sanacija

1333
01:42:04,080 --> 01:42:05,740
 u odnosu na superviziju

1334
01:42:05,740 --> 01:42:06,480
 jasno je da je

1335
01:42:06,480 --> 01:42:07,280
 ismeđu toga

1336
01:42:07,280 --> 01:42:08,720
 firewall, jel?

1337
01:42:08,720 --> 01:42:09,800
 Međutim,

1338
01:42:09,800 --> 01:42:11,640
 ja ću ipak uputiti

1339
01:42:11,640 --> 01:42:13,840
 jedno pitanje i vama.

1340
01:42:13,840 --> 01:42:15,020
 Naime,

1341
01:42:15,020 --> 01:42:17,680
 moramo biti iskreni

1342
01:42:17,680 --> 01:42:18,360
 i reći da

1343
01:42:18,360 --> 01:42:20,120
 mehanizam Bailina,

1344
01:42:20,120 --> 01:42:22,120
 ajmo bolje reći,

